1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,630
The most entertaining suspense
that predicts love.

2
00:00:02,630 --> 00:00:04,510
Love line prediction game, Heart Signal.

3
00:00:04,510 --> 00:00:08,180
Five people with sharp romance
radars have gathered.

4
00:00:08,180 --> 00:00:09,820
[The panel of five people is here]

5
00:00:09,820 --> 00:00:11,540
[Let's get it going]

6
00:00:11,540 --> 00:00:14,000
Last week, the female game-changer arrived.

7
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,300
A 26-year-old...

8
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:19,080
Korea University student and
a freelance designer, Choi So Yun.

9
00:00:19,080 --> 00:00:20,650
I feel bad for her.

10
00:00:20,650 --> 00:00:22,480
- You do?
- Really?

11
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:23,870
She likes Wu Yeol too much.

12
00:00:23,870 --> 00:00:25,360
She fell for him.

13
00:00:25,360 --> 00:00:27,630
How could she fall for him immediately?

14
00:00:27,630 --> 00:00:28,990
Everyone does, though.

15
00:00:28,990 --> 00:00:31,060
- Most of them do.
- It's true, but...

16
00:00:31,060 --> 00:00:35,020
- She falls in love in 3 seconds.
- I decide in the first 3 seconds.

17
00:00:35,020 --> 00:00:37,110
Right, she just needs 3 seconds.

18
00:00:37,110 --> 00:00:39,590
I think she fell for Wu Yeol in 3 seconds.

19
00:00:39,590 --> 00:00:43,510
He seems to get quick reactions from women.

20
00:00:43,510 --> 00:00:46,320
- We decided to acknowledge him.
- We do.

21
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:50,750
They look at him differently
once they talk to him.

22
00:00:50,750 --> 00:00:54,060
The one she fell for in 3 seconds
was Wu Yeol.

23
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:58,000
She sent the first text to Wu Yeol
and chose him as her date.

24
00:00:58,020 --> 00:00:59,450
We saw her leading for the first time.

25
00:00:59,450 --> 00:01:01,610
- And she switches things up quickly.
- "Should we talk casually?"

26
00:01:01,610 --> 00:01:02,880
I know.

27
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:07,040
I've never seen Wu Yeol like that.

28
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:12,710
He seemed to be leading with other women,

29
00:01:12,710 --> 00:01:14,830
but when So Yun suggested talking casually

30
00:01:14,830 --> 00:01:17,600
and asked him questions,

31
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:20,510
he seemed to be following her lead.

32
00:01:20,510 --> 00:01:22,990
He seemed adorable for once, right?

33
00:01:22,990 --> 00:01:25,580
He acted like a younger man
for the first time.

34
00:01:25,580 --> 00:01:31,650
I'm so excited because she won't
tiptoe around other women at all.

35
00:01:31,650 --> 00:01:34,440
- Right.
- It will get so fun.

36
00:01:34,440 --> 00:01:38,680
Yu Gyeong has been suppressing
her feelings for Wu Yeol,

37
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:40,910
but she came clean with Min Ju.
That was heartbreaking.

38
00:01:40,910 --> 00:01:44,250
I'm so annoyed.
He shouldn't be so pale, then.

39
00:01:44,250 --> 00:01:47,130
Or his lips shouldn't be so red.

40
00:01:47,130 --> 00:01:49,980
He has all the qualities she likes.

41
00:01:49,980 --> 00:01:52,680
I almost cried then.

42
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:56,270
It turns out she's very fragile.

43
00:01:56,270 --> 00:02:00,510
I fell for him so quickly.

44
00:02:00,510 --> 00:02:02,020
I shouldn't have.

45
00:02:02,020 --> 00:02:04,260
It was like song lyrics. "I shouldn't have."

46
00:02:04,260 --> 00:02:06,860
While talking to Min Ju,

47
00:02:06,860 --> 00:02:10,540
it sounded like she was deciding

48
00:02:10,540 --> 00:02:13,220
to be honest, although she was crying.

49
00:02:13,220 --> 00:02:16,990
I thought she might take her time,

50
00:02:16,990 --> 00:02:20,700
but she'll be expressing her feelings.

51
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:21,980
That could be.

52
00:02:21,980 --> 00:02:26,340
The tenants are leaving for
a small city in Japan, Tokushima.

53
00:02:26,340 --> 00:02:30,280
Let's check out what will happen there.

54
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:35,510
[The night before the trip to Tokushima]

55
00:02:35,510 --> 00:02:38,090
Let's start packing now.

56
00:02:39,150 --> 00:02:41,500
This is so nice.

57
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:44,950
Let's watch it for a bit.

58
00:02:44,950 --> 00:02:47,950
They listen to ballads a lot.

59
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:53,900
It's Seo Won.

60
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:55,780
You're zoning out.

61
00:02:56,610 --> 00:02:58,930
They're so cute.

62
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,750
You're good.

63
00:03:01,750 --> 00:03:04,170
I'll take requests.

64
00:03:04,170 --> 00:03:06,340
- So nice.
- Go one by one.

65
00:03:06,340 --> 00:03:08,490
I'll go first.

66
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:13,600
- "Lady in the Rainy Night."
- Yes, I love this.

67
00:03:15,590 --> 00:03:18,420
Why don't you just come here?

68
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,780
He's lost in thought.

69
00:03:20,780 --> 00:03:23,760
I had a tough time yesterday.

70
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:26,940
Yesterday? Really?

71
00:03:26,940 --> 00:03:28,750
[Gyu Ri was worried from the beginning]

72
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:31,180
But this is helpful.

73
00:03:31,180 --> 00:03:34,530
I can't wait for everyone to
discover this side of you.

74
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:44,070
People are starting to notice
that you're like that.

75
00:03:44,070 --> 00:03:48,430
We talked about it a bit yesterday.

76
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:53,000
They said you seemed the most serious.

77
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,300
[Glancing]

78
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:56,960
That's nice.

79
00:03:58,040 --> 00:04:00,380
Do you tend to cry a lot?

80
00:04:00,380 --> 00:04:03,700
- I already cried once.
- Really?

81
00:04:05,460 --> 00:04:10,760
When I don't get texts from
someone who used to text me...

82
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,910
Good, good.

83
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:19,600
[Seo Won is lost in thought]

84
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:22,900
It's making me want to work harder.

85
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:26,000
Seo Won knows what's going on.

86
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:31,130
- Love is all about determination.
- I knew you'd say that.

87
00:04:31,130 --> 00:04:33,740
I knew you'd say,
"Love is all about determination."

88
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:36,080
- Can I say one more thing?
- What is it?

89
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:38,690
Life is all about determination, too.

90
00:04:39,940 --> 00:04:43,360
- I love it. I love it.
- He's younger than her,

91
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:45,740
- but he's mature.
- He's a manly man.

92
00:04:45,740 --> 00:04:48,800
[What change will his determination bring?]

93
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:51,420
[Next is Yu Gyeong's song]

94
00:04:51,420 --> 00:04:54,230
["The Fool" by Jung Seung Hwan]

95
00:04:54,780 --> 00:04:57,020
This is driving me crazy.

96
00:04:57,840 --> 00:05:00,690
She's thinking about him.

97
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:04,590
[Yesterday morning]

98
00:05:05,730 --> 00:05:07,380
Nice bag.

99
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:08,840
Right?

100
00:05:09,550 --> 00:05:11,410
Nice scarf, too.

101
00:05:13,190 --> 00:05:15,770
[Complimenting nonchalantly]

102
00:05:15,770 --> 00:05:18,190
- Of course.
- Of course.

103
00:05:18,190 --> 00:05:19,700
Of course.

104
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:22,460
[The bag and scarf Wu Yeol complimented]

105
00:05:26,350 --> 00:05:30,080
[Hesitating]

106
00:05:34,630 --> 00:05:37,080
Are you going to school tomorrow, too?

107
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:38,950
- Am I coming here?
- Do you have school tomorrow?

108
00:05:38,950 --> 00:05:41,760
Yes, of course.

109
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:49,580
- How are you feeling?
- I feel better now.

110
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:59,790
[She can't stop thinking about one person]

111
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:05,000
[But why is it hard to act
according to how you feel?]

112
00:06:09,230 --> 00:06:11,250
[Crying]

113
00:06:11,250 --> 00:06:13,730
Gosh, it's upsetting.

114
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,470
- My goodness.
- Look at Min Ju.

115
00:06:17,470 --> 00:06:20,600
[The lyrics are relatable]

116
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:26,540
Should I bring you beer or something?

117
00:06:26,540 --> 00:06:28,670
Do you want me to?

118
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:31,630
No, it's okay.

119
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:36,200
What's with the lyrics?

120
00:06:37,060 --> 00:06:38,990
[No longer interested in packing]

121
00:06:38,990 --> 00:06:41,040
I can't get up.

122
00:06:43,510 --> 00:06:44,740
[Ta-da]

123
00:06:46,010 --> 00:06:50,100
[God. Wu. Yeol.]

124
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:54,080
[He's all you can think about right now]

125
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:57,330
[The two listened to music for a lot longer]

126
00:06:57,330 --> 00:06:59,500
[Jun Hyeon is on his way home]

127
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:02,200
[They calmed down to do the laundry]

128
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:04,150
[Going together]

129
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:07,840
Someone must be coming.

130
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:10,880
- You're dressed too cold.
- There they are.

131
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:13,450
Their timing is perfect.

132
00:07:13,450 --> 00:07:16,340
[Feels like they shouldn't
be looking at them]

133
00:07:16,340 --> 00:07:18,940
What's with this timing?

134
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:20,960
[Wu Yeol brought in So Yun's things]

135
00:07:23,930 --> 00:07:26,380
- You're back.
- Hello.

136
00:07:26,380 --> 00:07:28,690
Good work today.

137
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:39,700
- What did you...
- I had a date.

138
00:07:40,750 --> 00:07:42,630
Good going.

139
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:44,660
What's this? What did you do?

140
00:07:44,660 --> 00:07:47,910
Nice outfit. You were on a date, weren't you?

141
00:07:48,990 --> 00:07:51,110
- I'm back from work.
- Really? Just now?

142
00:07:51,110 --> 00:07:54,270
Seriously? Seriously?

143
00:07:54,270 --> 00:07:58,200
I decide in the first 3 seconds.

144
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:00,390
[Staring]

145
00:08:00,390 --> 00:08:02,100
Daebak.

146
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:08,060
Things keep getting tangled up
around Wu Yeol.

147
00:08:08,060 --> 00:08:10,360
[Detected her feelings
from the look in her eyes]

148
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,800
Did you decide?

149
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,770
Yes, I did.

150
00:08:21,740 --> 00:08:24,580
I need to pack.

151
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:27,260
[Wu Yeol is coming out to the living room]

152
00:08:27,260 --> 00:08:28,570
[Glancing]

153
00:08:33,850 --> 00:08:35,370
[Glancing]

154
00:08:38,650 --> 00:08:43,020
[Making eye contact without a word]

155
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:45,610
[Glancing]

156
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,450
[Smiling]

157
00:08:47,450 --> 00:08:49,850
[Mustering up the courage to approach him]

158
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:51,690
Long time no see.

159
00:08:51,690 --> 00:08:56,470
The slippers... There are no slippers.

160
00:08:56,470 --> 00:09:00,030
- They're small. They don't fit.
- Thank you.

161
00:09:01,350 --> 00:09:04,880
[She ends up coming back to the room]

162
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:11,280
[She wants to be courageous, but it's hard]

163
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:13,620
They're clean.

164
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:16,000
I packed three outfits.

165
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,950
What should I do now?

166
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:20,550
[Pacing around]

167
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,150
[Second attempt]

168
00:09:28,150 --> 00:09:30,120
What about the clothes?

169
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,590
- Hello.
- Hi.

170
00:09:32,590 --> 00:09:34,650
- Yu Gyeong, come here for a sec.
- Why?

171
00:09:34,650 --> 00:09:36,340
- Why didn't you tell me earlier?
- About what?

172
00:09:36,340 --> 00:09:38,780
That you had a date during the day.

173
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:41,230
- Where were you?
- Weren't you on a date earlier?

174
00:09:41,230 --> 00:09:43,230
- Where did you go?
- What are you talking about?

175
00:09:43,230 --> 00:09:45,060
Did you not?

176
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:46,890
Didn't you two have a date during the day?

177
00:09:46,890 --> 00:09:48,260
With me?

178
00:09:48,260 --> 00:09:51,180
- I thought you two had a date.
- Really?

179
00:09:51,180 --> 00:09:52,310
Sorry.

180
00:09:52,310 --> 00:09:55,010
- You're totally wrong.
- Sorry, sorry.

181
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:16,300
[She missed the moment]

182
00:10:18,890 --> 00:10:24,810
[The day before the trip is coming to an end]

183
00:10:27,290 --> 00:10:29,170
What should I pack?

184
00:10:30,290 --> 00:10:31,050
[Tap, tap]

185
00:10:31,050 --> 00:10:32,670
Unni, are you packing that, too?

186
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:35,320
Yes. If you put this on before the makeup,

187
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:37,000
the makeup absorbs so well.

188
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,590
That's crazy.

189
00:10:38,590 --> 00:10:42,120
I go to work early these days.

190
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:45,400
I wear this to make the makeup last.

191
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:48,330
- I should put it on, too.
- Try it.

192
00:10:48,330 --> 00:10:50,310
It doesn't hurt to start early.

193
00:10:50,310 --> 00:10:52,290
It's nice.

194
00:10:52,290 --> 00:10:57,110
[It's the morning of the trip]

195
00:11:01,130 --> 00:11:02,860
How exciting.

196
00:11:02,860 --> 00:11:04,230
Must be so nice.

197
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:07,380
[They arrived at the airport,
feeling excited]

198
00:11:07,380 --> 00:11:09,370
- Something hot?
- Something hot.

199
00:11:09,370 --> 00:11:10,990
That way.

200
00:11:13,170 --> 00:11:15,230
Did you research Tokushima?

201
00:11:15,230 --> 00:11:17,830
- Did you do research ahead?
- I'm a P.

202
00:11:17,830 --> 00:11:19,350
You're P. Got it.

203
00:11:19,350 --> 00:11:21,790
I go with the flow.

204
00:11:21,790 --> 00:11:23,290
You look so refreshed.

205
00:11:23,290 --> 00:11:25,000
Too fast? Sorry.

206
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,750
[So Yun's suitcase hit Min Ju's foot]

207
00:11:26,750 --> 00:11:28,400
- Are you okay?
- I'm okay.

208
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:31,030
Walk slowly.

209
00:11:31,030 --> 00:11:33,800
Tokushima is...

210
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,380
- Tokushima is famous for ramen.
- Really?

211
00:11:36,380 --> 00:11:37,850
- Really.
- Did you always know that?

212
00:11:37,850 --> 00:11:39,900
No, I watched YouTube yesterday.

213
00:11:40,670 --> 00:11:45,410
[Excited and on their way to check in]

214
00:11:45,410 --> 00:11:47,490
Gyu Ri and Seo Won are chatting.

215
00:11:47,490 --> 00:11:49,380
The seat assignment is important.

216
00:11:49,380 --> 00:11:51,260
We'll pick the seats first.

217
00:11:51,260 --> 00:11:54,560
The women will pick a pink slip.

218
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:56,460
Drawing lots?

219
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:58,280
- Want to pick first, Hyung?
- Should I?

220
00:11:58,280 --> 00:11:59,970
Why are you hiding it?

221
00:11:59,970 --> 00:12:03,300
- You looked, didn't you?
- How could I have?

222
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:05,960
- How nerve-racking.
- The number has to match, right?

223
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:07,770
Right, the number.

224
00:12:07,770 --> 00:12:09,650
- 26.
- What's your number, Gyu Ri?

225
00:12:09,650 --> 00:12:15,070
[Who will they be sitting next to?]

226
00:12:15,070 --> 00:12:17,500
- Should we find out later?
- Let's sit first.

227
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:19,810
Let's just go to our seats.

228
00:12:19,810 --> 00:12:23,850
[Waiting after dropping off the luggage]

229
00:12:32,140 --> 00:12:33,040
[Glancing]

230
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:40,260
[Feeling nervous for some reason]

231
00:12:42,820 --> 00:12:46,660
[Finishing the last boarding step]

232
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:49,840
- You can board early.
- Okay.

233
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:52,170
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

234
00:12:59,490 --> 00:13:02,830
[A two-hour flight]

235
00:13:02,830 --> 00:13:07,130
[Who will they end up with?]

236
00:13:08,330 --> 00:13:10,730
Geez Louise.

237
00:13:10,730 --> 00:13:12,710
- Where are they sitting?
- I wonder.

238
00:13:12,710 --> 00:13:14,310
Should I go in?

239
00:13:15,140 --> 00:13:16,210
Want to take the aisle seat?

240
00:13:16,210 --> 00:13:18,850
Seong Min is disappointed
to see Yu Gyeong pass by.

241
00:13:18,850 --> 00:13:22,330
[Yu Gyeong's seat buddy is Wu Yeol]

242
00:13:22,330 --> 00:13:24,040
- Gosh!
- Who's he sitting with?

243
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:25,520
Yu Gyeong?

244
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:27,480
[Head bumping]

245
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:30,360
[Smiling]

246
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:33,810
[They happen to be sitting together]

247
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:42,550
[What will happen?]

248
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:46,190
- They're sitting together like in a drama.
- I know.

249
00:13:46,190 --> 00:13:48,560
We'll close the gate and take off.

250
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:51,030
Please be seated.

251
00:13:51,030 --> 00:13:52,990
Is it in?

252
00:13:52,990 --> 00:13:54,010
[Getting up]

253
00:13:54,030 --> 00:13:55,300
I'm sorry.

254
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:57,740
That's right. Look how tall he is.

255
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:14,460
[Looking to the side]

256
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:23,070
I see how it is.

257
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:25,190
They need to clear the air.

258
00:14:25,190 --> 00:14:27,630
[Jun Hyeon is sitting next to Min Ju]

259
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:32,030
Yes, Jun Hyeon...

260
00:14:32,030 --> 00:14:34,720
[The night of their first date]

261
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:39,490
I thought I had a nice
conversation with Jun Hyeon.

262
00:14:39,490 --> 00:14:45,890
But he thought we might not be able to have

263
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:50,800
a deep conversation. Because of that,

264
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:54,650
I'm worried that I might've messed up.

265
00:14:54,650 --> 00:15:00,350
[Can they straighten things out?]

266
