474
00:26:36,300 --> 00:26:37,770
Here we go.

475
00:26:37,770 --> 00:26:39,510
Already?

476
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:44,270
- Thank you.
- Wow, the smell.

477
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:47,500
- Salt ramen.
- Looks delicious.

478
00:26:47,500 --> 00:26:49,120
[Smiling]

479
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:51,280
Looks tasty.

480
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:53,700
Thank you.

481
00:26:53,700 --> 00:26:56,920
Thank you for the meal. I'll take a photo.

482
00:26:57,800 --> 00:26:59,300
Take one for me.

483
00:26:59,300 --> 00:27:01,490
One, two, three.

484
00:27:01,490 --> 00:27:04,240
[A group shot]

485
00:27:04,240 --> 00:27:05,930
Let's eat.

486
00:27:05,930 --> 00:27:07,330
- Enjoy.
- We can eat now.

487
00:27:07,330 --> 00:27:08,950
[Big bite]

488
00:27:08,950 --> 00:27:11,090
It looks tasty.

489
00:27:13,380 --> 00:27:16,210
[They sound impressed]

490
00:27:16,210 --> 00:27:18,180
It has a skin.

491
00:27:18,180 --> 00:27:20,000
[Slurp]

492
00:27:21,020 --> 00:27:23,590
It's so delicious.

493
00:27:27,560 --> 00:27:29,400
[Eyebrows furling]

494
00:27:30,130 --> 00:27:31,660
[Hehe]

495
00:27:31,660 --> 00:27:34,990
The eyebrows don't lie.
The eyebrows don't lie.

496
00:27:38,690 --> 00:27:40,960
It's so delicious.

497
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:43,010
So nutty.

498
00:27:43,010 --> 00:27:48,190
[They're speechless]

499
00:27:49,530 --> 00:27:50,900
[Mmm]

500
00:27:50,900 --> 00:27:54,150
[While enjoying the ramen,
the next dish is being prepared]

501
00:27:54,940 --> 00:27:57,970
- Looks tasty.
- The Japanese tempura is the best.

502
00:27:57,970 --> 00:28:00,620
[Preparing with care]

503
00:28:01,340 --> 00:28:04,010
[All exclaiming]

504
00:28:04,010 --> 00:28:07,370
- Looks great.
- Sweet potato tempura.

505
00:28:08,070 --> 00:28:10,390
Thank you.

506
00:28:10,390 --> 00:28:12,650
A sea bream set.

507
00:28:13,590 --> 00:28:15,980
They plated them so nicely.

508
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:20,700
The chicken skin.

509
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:23,880
The one under the croquette?

510
00:28:25,050 --> 00:28:27,120
- It's chewy.
- It's delicious.

511
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:29,970
- And it's so juicy.
- The sauce?

512
00:28:31,050 --> 00:28:32,770
[Yum]

513
00:28:32,770 --> 00:28:35,030
- It's so good.
- It's really good.

514
00:28:35,030 --> 00:28:39,180
- Really?
- I've never had anything like this.

515
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:42,490
- Let's cut it in half.
- Sounds good.

516
00:28:42,490 --> 00:28:44,460
Do you want to cut with this?

517
00:28:45,370 --> 00:28:47,520
What are we doing today?

518
00:28:47,520 --> 00:28:49,730
What should we do?

519
00:28:52,830 --> 00:28:55,760
