537
00:29:55,260 --> 00:29:57,580
- Where were you?
- Weren't you on a date earlier?

538
00:29:57,580 --> 00:29:59,210
Where did you go?

539
00:29:59,210 --> 00:30:01,930
It's bothering him.

540
00:30:03,120 --> 00:30:05,180
This is bad.

541
00:30:06,580 --> 00:30:09,130
How should we decide?

542
00:30:09,130 --> 00:30:11,830
Should we just pick someone?

543
00:30:13,940 --> 00:30:18,870
- Do you guys want to choose first?
- What?

544
00:30:18,870 --> 00:30:20,890
- Rock, paper, and scissors?
- Why don't you discuss...

545
00:30:20,890 --> 00:30:24,310
and tell us what you agreed on?

546
00:30:25,510 --> 00:30:29,560
Men will choose today,
and women will choose tomorrow.

547
00:30:30,880 --> 00:30:32,220
[Glancing]

548
00:30:38,670 --> 00:30:43,840
[Exchanging eye contact, feeling tense]

549
00:30:43,900 --> 00:30:51,200
But I didn't get to talk to Min Ju a lot.

550
00:30:52,900 --> 00:30:55,340
I want to spend this evening with her.

551
00:30:56,250 --> 00:30:59,360
[Seo Won broke the silence with his choice]

552
00:31:01,250 --> 00:31:03,750
I choose Yu Gyeong.

553
00:31:06,340 --> 00:31:08,140
I never got to talk to her.

554
00:31:08,140 --> 00:31:09,500
What's he talking about?

555
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:11,780
Didn't they talk the most?

556
00:31:11,780 --> 00:31:13,620
Gosh, Seong Min.

557
00:31:13,620 --> 00:31:14,960
He went for it.

558
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:18,030
- He said he never talked to Yu Gyeong.
- I know.

559
00:31:23,260 --> 00:31:25,060
I choose Yu Gyeong, too.

560
00:31:25,060 --> 00:31:26,900
Jun Hyeon.

561
00:31:26,900 --> 00:31:29,980
[Seong Min and Jun Hyeon chose Yu Gyeong]

562
00:31:30,580 --> 00:31:31,520
[Glancing]

563
00:31:31,520 --> 00:31:33,710
The vibe changed.

564
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:39,100
I also want someone I haven't talked to.

565
00:31:39,140 --> 00:31:41,820
Someone he hasn't talked to?

566
00:31:42,380 --> 00:31:43,160
[Glancing]

567
00:31:44,190 --> 00:31:47,230
[Who's Wu Yeol leaning toward?]

568
00:31:47,990 --> 00:31:50,280
He keeps looking at him.

569
00:31:59,800 --> 00:32:05,100
Should we talk outside after we eat, then?

570
00:32:06,160 --> 00:32:08,360
Freestyle?

571
00:32:11,280 --> 00:32:14,850
[The unexpected honesty is
making everyone quiet]

572
00:32:18,230 --> 00:32:22,950
Let's eat first and talk a bit outside.

573
00:32:22,950 --> 00:32:24,980
Should we decide then?

574
00:32:26,020 --> 00:32:28,400
He looks serious.

575
00:32:28,400 --> 00:32:32,100
[They aren't able to talk freely]

576
00:32:32,100 --> 00:32:35,020
I'm getting indigestion watching them.

577
00:32:45,270 --> 00:32:50,980
I don't think this is right.
I don't know about this.

578
00:32:52,860 --> 00:32:54,210
[Glancing]

579
00:32:54,210 --> 00:32:57,740
- He's powerful.
- Well, I can't tell.

580
00:32:57,740 --> 00:32:58,670
[Glancing]

581
00:32:59,650 --> 00:33:01,270
[Staring]

582
00:33:05,570 --> 00:33:08,110
She's nervous. She's nervous.

583
00:33:11,790 --> 00:33:12,860
[Glancing]

584
00:33:13,440 --> 00:33:16,490
[They keep making eye contact]

585
00:33:18,070 --> 00:33:20,370
What is it? Why?

586
00:33:20,400 --> 00:33:23,600
What do you mean, exactly?

587
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:28,250
We can talk again if you're unhappy.

588
00:33:28,250 --> 00:33:30,560
[Wrapping herself up]

589
00:33:30,560 --> 00:33:31,620
[Shaking head]

590
00:33:31,620 --> 00:33:33,640
- First come first serve?
- It's chaos.

591
00:33:33,640 --> 00:33:36,560
- First come first serve?
- Why did you turn red?

592
00:33:36,560 --> 00:33:39,120
[Blushing at the sudden turn of events]

593
00:33:45,690 --> 00:33:50,240
[The women can't seem to talk]

594
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:51,890
[Pouty]

595
00:33:54,150 --> 00:33:56,730
- How about we...
- Let's discuss.

596
00:33:56,730 --> 00:33:58,400
Let's do that first.

597
00:33:58,400 --> 00:34:00,000
- Okay.
- Sounds good.

598
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:01,940
[The men will discuss and decide]

599
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:05,700
- Where will you discuss? Here?
- No.

600
00:34:05,700 --> 00:34:08,550
- Outside?
- Outside?

601
00:34:09,930 --> 00:34:12,770
Let's have a chat among men.

602
00:34:12,770 --> 00:34:14,260
- Here?
- Yes.

603
00:34:14,260 --> 00:34:15,470
Outside?

604
00:34:15,470 --> 00:34:19,050
Are you letting us decide, then?

605
00:34:19,050 --> 00:34:22,840
It'd be too complicated
if we discussed it, too.

606
00:34:22,840 --> 00:34:26,230
- Let's just go with their decision.
- We'll never agree.

607
00:34:26,230 --> 00:34:28,120
Let's go with their decision.

608
00:34:28,120 --> 00:34:29,850
We'll decide today, then.

609
00:34:29,850 --> 00:34:31,780
- We'll choose.
- We'll discuss first.

610
00:34:31,780 --> 00:34:33,950
- Let's step out.
- Let's go.

611
00:34:33,950 --> 00:34:36,790
This is a fun new rule.

612
00:34:38,330 --> 00:34:41,780
[Leaving to discuss briefly]

613
00:34:41,780 --> 00:34:44,390
Should we go down there?

614
00:34:45,040 --> 00:34:49,460
[Closing eyes while waiting nervously]

615
00:34:50,450 --> 00:34:53,360
[Their first dates in Japan]

616
00:34:53,810 --> 00:34:56,920
[Who will they create memories with?]

617
00:34:56,920 --> 00:34:59,740
- So scary.
- Oh, my God.

618
00:34:59,740 --> 00:35:01,210
So suspenseful.

619
00:35:01,210 --> 00:35:04,120
- We look to the side a lot.
- I know.

620
00:35:04,120 --> 00:35:07,020
They do it subtly to go unnoticed.

621
00:35:07,020 --> 00:35:09,480
- But it contains their emotions.
- It does.

622
00:35:09,480 --> 00:35:12,030
Min Ju and Yu Gyeong
know how each other feels.

623
00:35:12,030 --> 00:35:15,340
- I know.
- They can't maintain a poker face.

624
00:35:15,340 --> 00:35:19,250
This is terrible. Min Ju has
been helping Yu Gyeong.

625
00:35:19,250 --> 00:35:23,740
The men have been observing so far,

626
00:35:23,740 --> 00:35:25,950
but they think this trip is a momentum.

627
00:35:25,950 --> 00:35:29,760
Right. For the first time, Jun Hyeon said,
"I choose Yu Gyeong, too."

628
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:32,190
"Too" was the important word.

629
00:35:32,190 --> 00:35:35,480
It became clear.
Yu Gyeong is No. 1 right now.

630
00:35:35,480 --> 00:35:40,460
We were wrong to think he cares
about the age difference.

631
00:35:40,460 --> 00:35:44,620
I think he's been taking
his time because of that.

632
00:35:44,620 --> 00:35:46,890
He talks to everyone first.

633
00:35:46,890 --> 00:35:49,200
Because he doesn't want to be hasty.

634
00:35:49,200 --> 00:35:52,570
After talking to everyone,
he's sticking with Yu Gyeong.

635
00:35:52,570 --> 00:35:54,680
She's a lot younger than he is.

636
00:35:54,680 --> 00:35:56,870
He was hesitant for that reason,

637
00:35:56,870 --> 00:36:00,170
but he decided she was
still the one, and he said,

638
00:36:00,170 --> 00:36:01,770
"I choose Yu Gyeong, too."

639
00:36:01,770 --> 00:36:07,570
I think he decided to express
his feelings on this trip.

640
00:36:07,570 --> 00:36:10,630
In Korea, they had stuff to do

641
00:36:10,630 --> 00:36:12,260
and they had their jobs, too.

642
00:36:12,260 --> 00:36:14,860
Even if they didn't connect,

643
00:36:14,860 --> 00:36:17,710
since they had other things to do,

644
00:36:17,710 --> 00:36:19,470
they have excuses.

645
00:36:19,470 --> 00:36:22,820
But everyone is free since they're on a trip.

646
00:36:22,820 --> 00:36:26,290
Based on who they spend time with there,

647
00:36:26,290 --> 00:36:29,200
the relationships will change a lot.

648
00:36:29,200 --> 00:36:33,560
That's what makes this trip unpredictable.

649
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:37,620
[Seong Min and Yu Gyeong's first date]

650
00:36:41,270 --> 00:36:43,020
Rock, paper, scissors.

651
00:36:43,020 --> 00:36:44,580
It's just today.

652
00:36:45,450 --> 00:36:47,340
[Why did Seong Min have to win?]

653
00:36:47,340 --> 00:36:49,850
[Next time for Jun Hyeon and Yu Gyeong...]

654
00:36:52,430 --> 00:36:54,620
What do you think?

655
00:36:54,620 --> 00:36:56,740
About what?

656
00:36:56,740 --> 00:36:58,780
Japan.

657
00:37:00,740 --> 00:37:02,200
[Humming]

658
00:37:04,920 --> 00:37:08,860
We usually visit the big cities in Japan.

659
00:37:08,860 --> 00:37:10,640
Walk this way.

660
00:37:11,510 --> 00:37:14,650
We're in downtown, but it's not too noisy.

661
00:37:14,650 --> 00:37:17,090
- Right.
- It feels different.

662
00:37:19,240 --> 00:37:22,640
- Hello.
- Hello.

663
00:37:24,640 --> 00:37:28,150
Cocoa. I want the hot cocoa.

664
00:37:28,150 --> 00:37:30,130
What about this? Do you not want it?

665
00:37:30,130 --> 00:37:32,390
I don't think we need it.

666
00:37:32,390 --> 00:37:34,490
- You'll eat it if I order it, right?
- Of course.

667
00:37:34,490 --> 00:37:36,520
What would you like, then?

668
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:39,390
Strawberry.

669
00:37:39,390 --> 00:37:41,970
- The cheesecake.
- Cheesecake.

670
00:37:42,780 --> 00:37:46,100
And cocoa... One hot cocoa.

671
00:37:46,100 --> 00:37:49,980
One iced coffee, please.

672
00:37:49,980 --> 00:37:51,920
Did you get to rest in the car?

673
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:53,480
I slept the whole time.

674
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:55,570
- Ta-da.
- Wow.

675
00:37:55,570 --> 00:37:58,180
- Everyone slept.
- They're fast asleep.

676
00:38:00,070 --> 00:38:02,720
[Everyone fell asleep together]

677
00:38:03,570 --> 00:38:06,630
When I was sleeping, I kept...

678
00:38:06,630 --> 00:38:08,760
- You know this, right?
- You flinched?

679
00:38:08,760 --> 00:38:11,060
I kept hitting Gyu Ri next to me.

680
00:38:11,060 --> 00:38:13,310
I was like, "Sorry, Unni."

681
00:38:13,310 --> 00:38:15,900
I hit So Yun and went, "Sorry, Unni."

682
00:38:15,900 --> 00:38:18,480
You really are the youngest.

683
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:21,850
I only keep older female friends.

684
00:38:21,850 --> 00:38:24,700
- I keep older male friends.
- Really?

685
00:38:24,700 --> 00:38:26,630
They're all older men.

686
00:38:27,580 --> 00:38:30,000
- The way he looks at her...
- He's smitten.

687
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:32,690
You feel pressured, don't you?

688
00:38:32,690 --> 00:38:34,980
- A little?
- A little?

689
00:38:34,980 --> 00:38:38,980
You can say this is our first time
talking to each other.

690
00:38:38,980 --> 00:38:42,190
- She was sick the first time.
- You can say that.

691
00:38:42,190 --> 00:38:44,580
- Awkward. Awkward.
- So awkward.

692
00:38:44,580 --> 00:38:47,380
What's this now?

693
00:38:47,380 --> 00:38:50,400
I'm embarrassed. I'm shy.

694
00:38:50,400 --> 00:38:51,380
[Smiling]

695
00:38:51,380 --> 00:38:54,670
It's been like this since Day 1
for some reason.

696
00:38:54,670 --> 00:38:59,950
We've always been teasing each other.

697
00:38:59,950 --> 00:39:01,440
But when we went to get medicine...

698
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:03,910
We haven't talked this much before, have we?

699
00:39:03,910 --> 00:39:06,330
No, except for the first day.

700
00:39:06,330 --> 00:39:07,650
Right. The first day.

701
00:39:07,650 --> 00:39:11,500
We haven't had a chance to talk since then.

702
00:39:11,500 --> 00:39:13,000
Right.

703
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:15,040
We didn't.

704
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:18,710
That's when I first considered.

705
00:39:18,710 --> 00:39:22,590
But we got a chance in Japan.

706
00:39:22,590 --> 00:39:25,710
- I'm happy about it.
- It feels meaningful.

707
00:39:26,550 --> 00:39:29,700
I was curious what kind of person you are.

708
00:39:29,700 --> 00:39:31,850
That's why I requested a one-on-one.

709
00:39:31,850 --> 00:39:34,900
- Here's the request card.
- I request a one-on-one.

710
00:39:34,900 --> 00:39:36,690
I accept.

711
00:39:36,690 --> 00:39:39,090
[They have a similar sense of humor]

712
00:39:39,090 --> 00:39:42,770
I would've requested it tomorrow
if I had known it'd be so short.

713
00:39:42,770 --> 00:39:44,460
Because it's late in the evening.

714
00:39:44,460 --> 00:39:48,070
I looked up a lot of spots earlier.

715
00:39:48,070 --> 00:39:50,060
Oh, because we can't go?

716
00:39:50,060 --> 00:39:52,020
But it's okay that we can't.

717
00:39:52,020 --> 00:39:57,170
But the men chose their dates.

718
00:39:57,170 --> 00:39:58,310
Yes.

719
00:39:58,310 --> 00:40:01,880
I think that, in itself, is very meaningful.

720
00:40:01,880 --> 00:40:05,070
- Because we chose?
- Yes.

721
00:40:05,070 --> 00:40:09,410
And you decided to choose me.

722
00:40:09,410 --> 00:40:12,030
- In my face.
- In your face?

723
00:40:12,030 --> 00:40:13,910
I wanted to hide.

724
00:40:13,910 --> 00:40:18,480
- You wanted to hide?
- Because Seo Won said,

725
00:40:18,480 --> 00:40:21,560
"I want to talk to Min Ju" first.

726
00:40:21,560 --> 00:40:23,340
We didn't get to talk much.

727
00:40:23,340 --> 00:40:25,450
That's when I was like, "Wow!"

728
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:28,020
"I can't handle this."

729
00:40:28,020 --> 00:40:32,030
- The touchy situation.
- You mean the intense situation?

730
00:40:32,030 --> 00:40:33,430
Yes.

731
00:40:33,430 --> 00:40:36,110
My face was about to explode.

732
00:40:36,110 --> 00:40:40,210
And I was like, "I choose Yu Gyeong, then."

733
00:40:40,210 --> 00:40:41,580
[LOL]

734
00:40:42,260 --> 00:40:44,310
- I was bold.
- You really are.

735
00:40:44,310 --> 00:40:47,460
Of course. I'm from Gyeongsang-do.

736
00:40:49,470 --> 00:40:51,930
You like carbs. Bread and stuff like that.

737
00:40:51,930 --> 00:40:53,620
I think so.

738
00:40:53,620 --> 00:40:55,820
- I'll eat all of it.
- Go ahead.

739
00:40:55,820 --> 00:40:58,030
He won't stop looking at her.

740
00:40:58,030 --> 00:40:59,400
Do you not eat much?

741
00:40:59,400 --> 00:41:04,930
I don't get a lot of joy from eating.

742
00:41:04,930 --> 00:41:07,780
- Really?
- Not a lot. Not a lot.

743
00:41:07,780 --> 00:41:10,700
- I eat, but...
- You don't eat for survival, right?

744
00:41:10,700 --> 00:41:13,900
Not that extreme. I still like tasty food.

745
00:41:13,900 --> 00:41:16,610
- Try it.
- Thank you.

746
00:41:16,610 --> 00:41:18,590
[Yum]

747
00:41:18,590 --> 00:41:20,060
What do you think?

748
00:41:20,060 --> 00:41:21,700
[Loving it]

749
00:41:21,700 --> 00:41:25,600
- So cute.
- It's so moist and creamy.

750
00:41:25,600 --> 00:41:26,890
[She drops]

751
00:41:26,890 --> 00:41:30,750
- Gosh.
- Where's a napkin?

752
00:41:30,750 --> 00:41:31,830
Gosh.

753
00:41:32,690 --> 00:41:34,770
I'm okay.

754
00:41:34,770 --> 00:41:38,900
Are there napkins in the other room?

755
00:41:40,190 --> 00:41:42,220
I find stuff like this funny.

756
00:41:42,220 --> 00:41:43,980
- I'm sorry.
- What?

757
00:41:43,980 --> 00:41:47,390
I find you funny, but in a good way.

758
00:41:47,390 --> 00:41:50,050
I totally aspire to be funny.

759
00:41:50,050 --> 00:41:52,700
- But I'm a bit clumsy.
- Right.

760
00:41:52,700 --> 00:41:55,500
So, I couldn't discover my talent.

761
00:41:55,500 --> 00:41:59,520
- But you definitely have a talent.
- Really?

762
00:41:59,520 --> 00:42:02,650
Like how you said "Oh, eh" earlier.

763
00:42:02,650 --> 00:42:05,530
I don't know. I find stuff like that funny.

764
00:42:05,530 --> 00:42:07,680
But...

765
00:42:07,680 --> 00:42:11,640
- You find me funny?
- Not funny haha.

766
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:13,640
You just crack me up.

767
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:15,570
You could say we have a good rapport.

768
00:42:15,570 --> 00:42:17,850
We have a similar sense of humor.

769
00:42:17,850 --> 00:42:20,180
There's nothing bad about it.

770
00:42:20,180 --> 00:42:23,270
- Phew.
- There's nothing bad.

771
00:42:23,270 --> 00:42:25,300
I see.

772
00:42:26,420 --> 00:42:28,320
Everything is funny when you like someone.

773
00:42:28,320 --> 00:42:30,330
They're adorable even when they trip.

774
00:42:30,330 --> 00:42:33,170
- It's because he likes her.
- He does.

775
00:42:33,170 --> 00:42:36,840
What are you like normally?
I was curious about that.

776
00:42:36,840 --> 00:42:38,860
- What am I like?
- Yes.

777
00:42:38,860 --> 00:42:44,250
I'm definitely not an active person.

778
00:42:44,250 --> 00:42:48,590
But I'm social by nature.

779
00:42:48,590 --> 00:42:51,160
When I'm with someone I'm comfortable with.

780
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:54,560
- When I'm in a good mood, I...
- You scream?

781
00:42:54,560 --> 00:42:56,260
[Guilty]

782
00:42:56,260 --> 00:42:57,400
You're right.

783
00:42:57,400 --> 00:43:02,600
Like how we joke around normally.
Something like that.

784
00:43:02,600 --> 00:43:04,190
[Yum]

785
00:43:05,230 --> 00:43:06,980
Wow, daebak.

786
00:43:06,980 --> 00:43:09,900
- It's something like that.
- I just thought of this.

787
00:43:09,900 --> 00:43:13,490
I'm glad we came here. You look so happy.

788
00:43:13,490 --> 00:43:15,400
This is so tasty.

789
00:43:16,140 --> 00:43:18,360
You can have all of it.

790
00:43:20,630 --> 00:43:24,100
Wow, Seong Min's eyes are dripping honey.

791
00:43:24,100 --> 00:43:25,900
He's shooting heart signs.

792
00:43:25,900 --> 00:43:28,090
He'll wear off her face.

793
00:43:28,090 --> 00:43:32,820
I don't look like one,
but I'm a bit of a workaholic.

794
00:43:32,820 --> 00:43:38,360
How about when you rest
or something like that?

795
00:43:38,360 --> 00:43:41,570
I don't really rest.

796
00:43:41,570 --> 00:43:43,330
I always try to do something.

797
00:43:43,330 --> 00:43:45,770
I try to study on my day off.

798
00:43:45,770 --> 00:43:47,950
I usually work out.

799
00:43:47,950 --> 00:43:52,870
I struggle to rest for too long, I think.

800
00:43:52,870 --> 00:43:56,350
- He's passionate.
- I find people like that fascinating.

801
00:43:56,350 --> 00:43:58,450
I can stay home for about a week.

802
00:43:58,450 --> 00:44:01,420
- Really? Not go out at all?
- No.

803
00:44:01,420 --> 00:44:03,280
It's possible.

804
00:44:04,120 --> 00:44:06,150
She must've felt so stressed just now.

805
00:44:06,150 --> 00:44:09,780
- In a good way or a bad way?
- In a good way.

806
00:44:11,960 --> 00:44:15,700
I tend to press on the brake
to temper my feelings.

807
00:44:15,700 --> 00:44:17,540
- Huh?
- Why?

808
00:44:18,390 --> 00:44:21,850
When I start developing feelings,

809
00:44:21,900 --> 00:44:26,460
I brake and take a step back.

810
00:44:28,170 --> 00:44:29,780
[Pause]

811
00:44:29,780 --> 00:44:31,700
That's nice.

812
00:44:31,700 --> 00:44:33,610
I'm jealous.

813
00:44:35,010 --> 00:44:37,150
It's because I can't do that.

814
00:44:37,150 --> 00:44:39,550
- You just accelerate?
- I can't do it.

815
00:44:39,550 --> 00:44:43,280
- Your steering wheel broke?
- I drive slowly,

816
00:44:44,310 --> 00:44:47,360
- but I can't brake.
- You can't?

817
00:44:47,360 --> 00:44:51,790
But I'm actually trying to do that now.

818
00:44:51,790 --> 00:44:55,620
It's hard to control myself, but...

819
00:44:57,630 --> 00:45:00,070
Anyway, it's something like that.

820
00:45:01,800 --> 00:45:03,720
- Pardon?
- Huh?

821
00:45:03,720 --> 00:45:05,360
Didn't he mean he accelerates?

822
00:45:05,360 --> 00:45:07,350
What's he talking about?

823
00:45:07,350 --> 00:45:09,940
He can't brake by nature. What's the saying?

824
00:45:09,940 --> 00:45:12,800
He's just trying to say that he likes her.

825
00:45:12,800 --> 00:45:15,410
Even when she talks about someone else,

826
00:45:15,410 --> 00:45:17,930
he doesn't seem to care.

827
00:45:17,930 --> 00:45:19,020
Right, right.

828
00:45:19,020 --> 00:45:23,150
- Should we have sake next door?
- Sounds good.

829
00:45:23,150 --> 00:45:25,120
- Thank you for the meal.
- Is that right?

830
00:45:25,120 --> 00:45:27,780
- Thank you.
- Take care.

831
00:45:27,780 --> 00:45:31,230
- Thank you so much.
- Watch your step.

832
00:45:31,230 --> 00:45:35,070
What are you doing? You're so...

833
00:45:35,070 --> 00:45:38,160
I just told you to watch your step.

834
00:45:38,940 --> 00:45:42,230
- I warned you.
- You're so clumsy.

835
00:45:42,230 --> 00:45:43,970
- Am I clumsy?
- Yes.

836
00:45:43,970 --> 00:45:49,090
- Really?
- I notice gaps in you often.

837
00:45:49,090 --> 00:45:51,730
Gaps? Like the opening thread?

838
00:45:51,730 --> 00:45:54,060
- What?
- What?

839
00:45:54,060 --> 00:45:55,780
I sense the opening thread!

840
00:45:55,780 --> 00:45:57,330
Hinokami Kagura.

841
00:45:57,330 --> 00:45:59,360
They have that in common.

842
00:45:59,360 --> 00:46:00,920
I know Chainsaw Man, too.

843
00:46:00,920 --> 00:46:04,610
[Bonding over anime]

844
00:46:05,170 --> 00:46:07,360
[On the first night of the trip]

845
00:46:08,050 --> 00:46:11,670
[They're realizing they had a similar taste]

846
00:46:13,500 --> 00:46:15,100
So pretty.

847
00:46:15,130 --> 00:46:17,290
I like this road.

848
00:46:17,290 --> 00:46:19,860
- Are your shoes comfy?
- Yes.

849
00:46:19,860 --> 00:46:21,940
Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri.

850
00:46:21,940 --> 00:46:24,510
Should we each say who we want?

851
00:46:24,510 --> 00:46:25,750
- I want Yu Gyeong.
- I want Min Ju.

852
00:46:25,750 --> 00:46:27,680
I want Yu Gyeong.

853
00:46:28,960 --> 00:46:30,940
I'll go with Gyu Ri, then.

854
00:46:30,940 --> 00:46:33,130
- Gyu Ri?
- He's going back to Gyu Ri?

855
00:46:33,130 --> 00:46:35,440
Gosh, I'm not sure.

856
00:46:35,440 --> 00:46:38,470
[Gyu Ri and Wu Yeol were
facing each other earlier]

857
00:46:39,870 --> 00:46:51,530
[Feeling strangely nervous]

858
00:46:51,530 --> 00:46:54,380
- Gyu Ri?
- We're done, then. Right?

859
00:46:54,380 --> 00:46:56,080
It's just us, then.

860
00:46:56,080 --> 00:46:57,490
Rock, paper, scissors?

861
00:46:57,490 --> 00:47:00,030
- What do you think?
- Sounds good.

862
00:47:00,870 --> 00:47:02,700
Let's leave, then.

863
00:47:02,700 --> 00:47:04,490
You're leaving quickly.

864
00:47:04,490 --> 00:47:06,960
I'm totally decided.

865
00:47:08,550 --> 00:47:11,370
Gyu Ri, you're going with Wu Yeol.

866
00:47:12,530 --> 00:47:17,020
- Seong Min chose...
- Yu Gyeong.

867
00:47:17,020 --> 00:47:18,400
Did I say that already?

868
00:47:18,400 --> 00:47:20,710
I choose So Yun.

869
00:47:20,710 --> 00:47:24,120
- My gosh.
- Gosh, poor Yu Gyeong.

870
00:47:33,540 --> 00:47:36,680
[What kind of feelings will develop]

871
00:47:36,680 --> 00:47:42,670
[on the first day of the trip?]

872
00:47:42,670 --> 00:47:44,630
Wow.

873
00:47:46,530 --> 00:47:49,810
[Walking alone together
in Tokushima at night]

874
00:47:49,810 --> 00:47:51,870
It's pretty.

875
00:47:51,870 --> 00:47:53,570
So pretty.

876
00:47:54,340 --> 00:47:59,720
I think I made the right choice.

877
00:47:59,720 --> 00:48:02,550
My shoes and socks.

878
00:48:02,550 --> 00:48:05,300
- They suit you well.
- I like the combo.

879
00:48:05,300 --> 00:48:07,610
They talk to each other formally.

880
00:48:07,610 --> 00:48:10,360
- Should we...
- Yes?

881
00:48:14,200 --> 00:48:17,490
- try talking casually?
- Really?

882
00:48:17,490 --> 00:48:18,820
[Laughing]

883
00:48:18,820 --> 00:48:21,510
Gyu Ri is being proactive.

884
00:48:22,420 --> 00:48:25,440
Should we talk casually?

885
00:48:25,440 --> 00:48:26,820
Let's.

886
00:48:26,820 --> 00:48:28,400
I can do it now.

887
00:48:28,400 --> 00:48:31,860
It took a week to get adjusted.

888
00:48:31,860 --> 00:48:35,700
The city is so pretty and pleasant.

889
00:48:35,700 --> 00:48:37,140
[Ding-dong]

890
00:48:37,140 --> 00:48:39,490
I like that sound.

891
00:48:40,640 --> 00:48:41,920
[Grin]

892
00:48:43,350 --> 00:48:45,540
- Huh?
- Huh?

893
00:48:46,320 --> 00:48:49,840
I laughed. I laughed because it was funny.

894
00:48:49,840 --> 00:48:55,130
I thought you ignored me.

895
00:48:55,130 --> 00:48:58,090
- You forced me to answer.
- What did you say?

896
00:48:58,090 --> 00:49:00,470
I like it, too.

897
00:49:00,470 --> 00:49:04,180
- This is it, right?
- So exciting. What?

898
00:49:06,000 --> 00:49:07,630
Wow.

899
00:49:07,630 --> 00:49:10,100
Wow, what's that? A bar?

900
00:49:11,140 --> 00:49:14,680
Is it an izakaya? An omakase?

901
00:49:16,090 --> 00:49:17,680
[Wow]

902
00:49:22,930 --> 00:49:27,040
Wow. I'm so happy.

903
00:49:27,040 --> 00:49:30,200
[Sitting side by side]

904
00:49:30,200 --> 00:49:33,870
There are so many cute restaurants.

905
00:49:33,870 --> 00:49:39,220
If you look here, you can see their menu.

906
00:49:39,220 --> 00:49:41,400
Thank you.

907
00:49:41,400 --> 00:49:44,140
Let's order everything we want.

908
00:49:44,140 --> 00:49:48,080
- We didn't get to eat much earlier.
- Is this your treat?

909
00:49:48,080 --> 00:49:51,660
I heard you got paid today.

910
00:49:51,660 --> 00:49:55,370
This must be a drink.

911
00:49:59,780 --> 00:50:02,560
- Yakitori?
- Yes.

912
00:50:02,560 --> 00:50:05,080
Should we order different drinks?

913
00:50:05,080 --> 00:50:09,990
- What do you think?
- Let's start with draft beer.

914
00:50:09,990 --> 00:50:14,210
You get the most expensive sake
when you're clueless.

915
00:50:16,670 --> 00:50:19,930
- I've been wanting to drink with you.
- What? Come on.

916
00:50:19,930 --> 00:50:24,190
- Isn't it because I'm the best drinker?
- It's not like that.

917
00:50:27,240 --> 00:50:29,790
Do you not find me uncomfortable?

918
00:50:29,790 --> 00:50:32,450
- No, I don't.
- You don't?

919
00:50:32,450 --> 00:50:33,970
- Do you find me uncomfortable?
- No.

920
00:50:33,970 --> 00:50:35,250
- Is it okay?
- Yes.

921
00:50:35,250 --> 00:50:37,910
I don't feel uncomfortable, but...

922
00:50:37,910 --> 00:50:40,020
- You're worried that I do?
- Yes.

923
00:50:40,020 --> 00:50:42,900
Why? Why would I feel uncomfortable?

924
00:50:42,900 --> 00:50:46,280
Because I talk about serious things a lot?

925
00:50:46,280 --> 00:50:50,000
It's necessary. It is.

926
00:50:52,250 --> 00:50:56,570
But I want to see
a different side of you, too.

927
00:50:56,570 --> 00:51:01,340
I'm curious how you are
when you're excited, too.

928
00:51:01,340 --> 00:51:05,580
And I notice something every once in a while.

929
00:51:05,580 --> 00:51:09,180
- Really?
- I'm not sure if anyone else noticed it.

930
00:51:09,180 --> 00:51:11,580
Maybe it's because I try to be funny.

931
00:51:12,660 --> 00:51:15,620
But there's something only I noticed.

932
00:51:15,620 --> 00:51:17,770
[Curious]

933
00:51:18,740 --> 00:51:21,240
- You don't know, do you?
- No.

934
00:51:22,510 --> 00:51:23,830
I'll tell you later.

935
00:51:23,900 --> 00:51:27,500
[The moment he's been waiting for]

936
00:51:28,710 --> 00:51:31,720
- Let's raise our glasses.
- Shall we?

937
00:51:32,820 --> 00:51:34,370
[Cheers]

938
00:51:43,670 --> 00:51:47,130
My stomach hurt a bit today.

939
00:51:47,130 --> 00:51:50,300
So, I thought I shouldn't be drinking.

940
00:51:50,300 --> 00:51:52,330
Since when did it hurt?

941
00:51:52,330 --> 00:51:55,830
Earlier... Thank you.

942
00:51:55,830 --> 00:51:58,130
Looks tasty.

943
00:51:59,100 --> 00:52:00,950
Thank you.

944
00:52:01,740 --> 00:52:03,600
But I'm totally fine after taking medicine.

945
00:52:03,600 --> 00:52:05,180
So, I changed my mind.

946
00:52:05,180 --> 00:52:07,700
Whether I drink or not, I'll be sick anyway.

947
00:52:07,700 --> 00:52:10,180
[It's hard not to while traveling]

948
00:52:10,910 --> 00:52:13,810
When I'm in Japan, I eat like this,

949
00:52:13,810 --> 00:52:15,950
and eat again after walking around.

950
00:52:15,950 --> 00:52:19,650
And then eat street food again, usually.

951
00:52:21,490 --> 00:52:24,120
Aren't you rushing too much?

952
00:52:24,120 --> 00:52:26,190
I'm not sure.

953
00:52:30,180 --> 00:52:33,510
- Do you want this on your plate?
- I'd love it.

954
00:52:35,440 --> 00:52:37,290
[Big bite]

955
00:52:41,470 --> 00:52:45,970
Can we talk about something fun
when we're alone?

956
00:52:45,970 --> 00:52:49,390
Of course. Do you have something?

957
00:52:49,390 --> 00:52:52,850
- Yes.
- What is it?

958
00:52:59,230 --> 00:53:01,950
I...

959
00:53:03,370 --> 00:53:08,980
know what everyone's nickname is.

960
00:53:10,810 --> 00:53:12,930
Since when?

961
00:53:12,930 --> 00:53:15,870
I think I found out pretty quickly.

962
00:53:15,870 --> 00:53:20,320
You did because of the texts, right?

963
00:53:21,110 --> 00:53:22,170
[Side-eyes]

964
00:53:22,800 --> 00:53:26,100
Your eyes are too scary.

965
00:53:26,120 --> 00:53:27,690
[Glancing]

966
00:53:29,340 --> 00:53:31,430
[Turning]

967
00:53:33,900 --> 00:53:39,640
[She didn't get a text from Wu Yeol on Day 4]

968
00:53:39,640 --> 00:53:43,410
[Or the next day]

969
00:53:43,410 --> 00:53:44,560
[Or the next day]

970
00:53:44,560 --> 00:53:47,290
She hasn't gotten any for a while.

971
00:53:52,300 --> 00:53:54,740
But I don't like knowing.

972
00:53:57,410 --> 00:54:00,510
I think it's better not to know.

973
00:54:00,510 --> 00:54:02,380
I agree.

974
00:54:03,390 --> 00:54:06,190
- I think so, too.
- Cheers.

975
00:54:09,160 --> 00:54:13,170
- She knows the history.
- She knew whenever he texted.

976
00:54:13,170 --> 00:54:16,960
But she doesn't like being bothered by it.

977
00:54:16,960 --> 00:54:19,370
- Should I add everything?
- Yes.

978
00:54:19,370 --> 00:54:21,620
- Sea bream.
- Wow.

979
00:54:22,680 --> 00:54:24,880
I'll use both hands.

980
00:54:24,880 --> 00:54:27,510
I should've poured you a glass first.

981
00:54:27,510 --> 00:54:29,350
[Spilled a little]

982
00:54:29,350 --> 00:54:32,190
I knew this would happen.

983
00:54:34,670 --> 00:54:36,810
It's so sweet.

984
00:54:36,810 --> 00:54:38,650
- It's sweet.
- "It's sweet."

985
00:54:38,650 --> 00:54:41,150
It's so smooth.

986
00:54:41,150 --> 00:54:43,050
How do you want it?

987
00:54:43,050 --> 00:54:46,810
The broth first?
I'll serve you some with tongs later.

988
00:54:46,810 --> 00:54:48,890
Is there something you want?

989
00:54:48,890 --> 00:54:52,040
- I'll take the broth first.
- Mushrooms?

990
00:54:52,040 --> 00:54:54,840
I'll check if it's cooked later.

991
00:54:54,900 --> 00:54:58,760
Wu Yeol is acting differently.
He's so attentive.

992
00:54:58,760 --> 00:55:02,750
- He's trying to make an impression.
- He's so caring.

993
00:55:05,720 --> 00:55:07,800
[Serving]

994
00:55:09,840 --> 00:55:11,860
[Happy]

995
00:55:15,900 --> 00:55:21,110
I'm so curious who So Yun chose yesterday.

996
00:55:21,110 --> 00:55:23,190
Yesterday?

997
00:55:23,190 --> 00:55:24,240
[Pause]

998
00:55:24,240 --> 00:55:26,310
I know.

999
00:55:26,310 --> 00:55:27,130
[Side-eyes]

1000
00:55:27,130 --> 00:55:29,510
She's bothered by So Yun.

1001
00:55:30,970 --> 00:55:33,420
It's obvious.

1002
00:55:34,930 --> 00:55:38,400
I don't know. How would I know?

1003
00:55:38,400 --> 00:55:40,550
This is fun.

1004
00:55:42,770 --> 00:55:46,440
- I'm scared of you.
- Why? What are you scared of?

1005
00:55:46,440 --> 00:55:50,290
I find you the most difficult to read.

1006
00:55:50,290 --> 00:55:52,200
Really?

1007
00:55:52,200 --> 00:55:56,830
Yes. I won't be able to know everything,

1008
00:55:56,830 --> 00:56:01,300
but I find you the most difficult.

1009
00:56:01,300 --> 00:56:02,860
You're difficult for me.

1010
00:56:02,860 --> 00:56:06,260
She's starting to reveal her true feelings.

1011
00:56:18,040 --> 00:56:22,030
That's why I wanted to talk to you tonight.

1012
00:56:25,070 --> 00:56:30,620
I was hoping to see you relaxed, maybe?

1013
00:56:30,620 --> 00:56:34,130
I was hoping for something like that.

1014
00:56:35,690 --> 00:56:38,100
I wanted you to feel...

1015
00:56:40,610 --> 00:56:43,400
closer to me.

1016
00:56:44,900 --> 00:56:47,250
I think I've been hoping for that.

1017
00:56:47,250 --> 00:56:50,220
When we're all together,

1018
00:56:50,220 --> 00:56:56,810
we keep facing each other
in those situations.

1019
00:56:58,960 --> 00:57:01,970
It's so hard when we're all together.

1020
00:57:01,970 --> 00:57:04,050
I prefer being with you one-on-one.

1021
00:57:04,050 --> 00:57:07,130
Me, too. When we're with everyone else,

1022
00:57:07,130 --> 00:57:11,800
I don't want people to find out how I feel.

1023
00:57:13,470 --> 00:57:15,660
I was most curious about

1024
00:57:15,660 --> 00:57:19,320
whether you've been
with an older woman or not.

1025
00:57:21,570 --> 00:57:24,790
[Staring]

1026
00:57:27,500 --> 00:57:29,360
Older women?

1027
00:57:33,040 --> 00:57:36,170
I find older women easier to get along with.

1028
00:57:36,170 --> 00:57:39,010
He won't say he's only dated older women.

1029
00:57:39,010 --> 00:57:42,440
Does that mean you've been with one?

1030
00:57:42,440 --> 00:57:45,380
- Romantically, do you mean?
- Yes.

1031
00:57:52,510 --> 00:57:54,610
I have.

1032
00:57:56,700 --> 00:58:00,140
I was going to tell you to
be honest if you said no.

1033
00:58:00,140 --> 00:58:02,890
Of course, I've dated someone older.

1034
00:58:02,890 --> 00:58:05,570
That's why I find older women more...

1035
00:58:07,090 --> 00:58:09,270
Why? Why do you find them
easier to get along with?

1036
00:58:09,270 --> 00:58:10,750
[Curious]

1037
00:58:10,750 --> 00:58:14,860
I feel more at ease when I talk to them.

1038
00:58:14,860 --> 00:58:18,580
Until I moved into the house,

1039
00:58:18,580 --> 00:58:21,900
I've preferred older women.

1040
00:58:21,900 --> 00:58:24,480
- That's not what I'm asking.
- I know.

1041
00:58:24,480 --> 00:58:26,430
What about in the past?

1042
00:58:26,430 --> 00:58:30,470
For real. Have you dated many? A lot?

1043
00:58:30,470 --> 00:58:32,800
- Yes.
- You mean if I've dated many?

1044
00:58:32,800 --> 00:58:36,080
I haven't dated many people.

1045
00:58:36,080 --> 00:58:39,580
- I dated one person for a long time.
- Really?

1046
00:58:39,580 --> 00:58:42,590
She wasn't older. She was the same age.

1047
00:58:42,590 --> 00:58:44,890
It was recent.

1048
00:58:49,620 --> 00:58:52,870
I can't say
I have a lot of dating experience.

1049
00:58:52,870 --> 00:58:55,810
But some of them were older.

1050
00:59:02,160 --> 00:59:05,840
I've never dated a younger man.

1051
00:59:06,900 --> 00:59:09,420
- I can tell.
- You can, right?

1052
00:59:09,420 --> 00:59:15,780
Earlier, So Yun told me...

1053
00:59:17,360 --> 00:59:21,210
"Your face reading shows no younger men."

1054
00:59:22,900 --> 00:59:27,450
I thought it was so funny that she said that.

1055
00:59:27,450 --> 00:59:31,170
I wonder if other people think that, too.

1056
00:59:35,110 --> 00:59:37,180
It's hard to know.

1057
00:59:37,180 --> 00:59:41,770
Right, we won't know. But...

1058
00:59:41,770 --> 00:59:45,360
the fact that I haven't dated
one isn't important.

1059
00:59:45,360 --> 00:59:47,880
I don't care as long as he's mature.

1060
00:59:47,880 --> 00:59:50,280
- Right.
- But...

1061
00:59:50,280 --> 00:59:54,110
if I notice he isn't,

1062
00:59:55,300 --> 00:59:57,920
I'll think, "It's because he's young."

1063
00:59:57,920 --> 01:00:03,390
I haven't dated a younger woman before.

1064
01:00:03,390 --> 01:00:06,130
Until I moved into the house.

1065
01:00:06,130 --> 01:00:09,380
Because I thought they were immature,

1066
01:00:09,380 --> 01:00:12,210
I didn't keep younger women near me.

1067
01:00:13,200 --> 01:00:16,630
When it comes to romantic relationships?

1068
01:00:17,670 --> 01:00:21,680
But I realized that...

1069
01:00:21,680 --> 01:00:26,860
- each person is different.
- Right, right.

1070
01:00:29,920 --> 01:00:34,910
I think I no longer have that bias.

1071
01:00:36,630 --> 01:00:40,200
I'm attracted to someone
if I like them as a person.

1072
01:00:40,200 --> 01:00:43,060
Right. I learned that, too.

1073
01:00:44,250 --> 01:00:46,360
I agree.

1074
01:00:49,010 --> 01:00:51,350
[Nodding]

1075
01:00:52,550 --> 01:00:58,800
[The two seem lost in thought]

1076
01:00:58,800 --> 01:01:03,660
[Who are they thinking about?]

1077
01:01:03,660 --> 01:01:07,070
He's revealing a lot tonight.

1078
01:01:07,070 --> 01:01:08,760
Gyu Ri might feel concerned.

1079
01:01:08,760 --> 01:01:12,310
But you don't want to read too much into it.

1080
01:01:12,310 --> 01:01:14,680
- Are they your clothes?
- Yes.

1081
01:01:14,680 --> 01:01:18,210
Why do you not like your own clothes?

1082
01:01:18,210 --> 01:01:20,560
I wasn't wearing mine yesterday.

1083
01:01:20,560 --> 01:01:22,850
I don't have a strong taste,

1084
01:01:22,850 --> 01:01:25,190
but I dislike a lot of things.

1085
01:01:25,190 --> 01:01:28,350
- She was sitting in front of them.
- She could hear them.

1086
01:01:28,350 --> 01:01:29,530
[Thinking]

1087
01:01:30,100 --> 01:01:32,470
Isn't it nice to be called Oppa?

1088
01:01:32,470 --> 01:01:34,630
Huh? She's probing him.

1089
01:01:34,630 --> 01:01:36,160
[Flustered]

1090
01:01:36,900 --> 01:01:40,130
[Trying to sound him out]

1091
01:01:40,900 --> 01:01:42,790
Well...

1092
01:01:47,420 --> 01:01:49,920
[Concerned]

1093
01:01:52,780 --> 01:01:54,810
Should we raise our glasses?

1094
01:01:58,770 --> 01:02:01,480
I wonder if it's for that reason.

1095
01:02:01,480 --> 01:02:06,450
I wanted to go on another date with you.

1096
01:02:08,150 --> 01:02:13,560
I'm sure we'd be different
once we're totally close.

1097
01:02:13,560 --> 01:02:18,030
I wanted you to see a glimpse
of that side of me.

1098
01:02:18,030 --> 01:02:21,990
I'm sure I'll get to see
all the different sides of you.

1099
01:02:21,990 --> 01:02:26,620
But for both you and me,

1100
01:02:26,620 --> 01:02:28,590
we didn't reveal everything
about ourselves yet.

1101
01:02:28,590 --> 01:02:31,670
I wanted to show that side of me.

1102
01:02:31,670 --> 01:02:35,490
And I wanted to see that side of you, too.

1103
01:02:35,490 --> 01:02:37,320
[Staring]

1104
01:02:37,320 --> 01:02:40,610
I'm glad that we had a chance
to do that today.

1105
01:02:40,610 --> 01:02:43,330
He sure is serious.

1106
01:02:47,390 --> 01:02:49,680
But right now...

1107
01:02:49,680 --> 01:02:53,650
I think I'm myself right now.

1108
01:02:53,650 --> 01:02:56,260
The way I am right now.

1109
01:03:01,440 --> 01:03:03,040
I wanted to call you by your name.

1110
01:03:03,040 --> 01:03:05,720
"I wanted to call you by your name"!

1111
01:03:05,720 --> 01:03:07,360
While speaking casually?

1112
01:03:07,360 --> 01:03:11,520
[Casual speaking flirting]

1113
01:03:11,520 --> 01:03:12,870
[Taken aback]

1114
01:03:12,870 --> 01:03:16,460
You're so daring.

1115
01:03:17,720 --> 01:03:19,840
That came out of nowhere.

1116
01:03:19,840 --> 01:03:21,580
[Grin]

1117
01:03:24,730 --> 01:03:29,190
[Oh, my goodness!]

1118
01:03:29,190 --> 01:03:32,080
- Is it flirting?
- Huge!

1119
01:03:32,080 --> 01:03:33,460
It's huge.

1120
01:03:33,460 --> 01:03:36,170
I want to watch that again.

1121
01:03:36,170 --> 01:03:37,470
I'm worried about tomorrow.

1122
01:03:37,470 --> 01:03:42,690
I feel like women
will get to choose tomorrow.

1123
01:03:42,690 --> 01:03:45,770
- Will you choose me?
- My gosh!

1124
01:03:45,770 --> 01:03:48,030
[Flustered]

1125
01:03:48,030 --> 01:03:50,960
You're doing this on purpose, aren't you?

1126
01:03:55,000 --> 01:03:56,970
If I have fun tonight.

1127
01:03:56,970 --> 01:03:59,030
I'm going crazy.

1128
01:03:59,030 --> 01:04:07,030
[Feeling a little tipsy,
their hearts flutter even more]

1129
01:04:11,070 --> 01:04:14,190
How should I say this?
I don't usually believe in fate.

1130
01:04:14,190 --> 01:04:17,970
But for some reason...
I don't believe it, but...

1131
01:04:17,970 --> 01:04:19,440
Are we talking fate here?

1132
01:04:19,440 --> 01:04:25,100
let's say I end up with someone
who's not my first choice.

1133
01:04:25,100 --> 01:04:27,040
But even so...

1134
01:04:28,030 --> 01:04:33,310
But even so, if I get to spend
tomorrow like that,

1135
01:04:34,890 --> 01:04:39,560
we still have a lot of time left
when we return to Korea.

1136
01:04:39,560 --> 01:04:45,800
I wonder if I should...

1137
01:04:45,800 --> 01:04:51,830
put everything on the line for one day.

1138
01:04:51,830 --> 01:04:54,660
Makes me think that.

1139
01:04:54,660 --> 01:05:00,470
I feel like if we're meant to
be together, it will happen.

1140
01:05:00,470 --> 01:05:03,720
I guess I started to believe in fate?

1141
01:05:03,720 --> 01:05:07,150
[If we're meant to be...]

1142
01:05:07,150 --> 01:05:09,730
[we'll be together]

1143
01:05:09,730 --> 01:05:13,250
She's not jumping at what Wu Yeol said.

1144
01:05:15,350 --> 01:05:17,280
It's hard.

1145
01:05:17,280 --> 01:05:19,880
I know. It's hard.

1146
01:05:19,880 --> 01:05:24,350
Do you have another bucket list
while in the house?

1147
01:05:25,950 --> 01:05:27,030
Yeah.

1148
01:05:27,030 --> 01:05:30,510
[Curious]

1149
01:05:30,510 --> 01:05:35,490
You know the movie with
that actor, Koo Kyo Hwan?

1150
01:05:35,490 --> 01:05:39,130
- "Once We Were Us"?
- Yes, I want to see that.

1151
01:05:40,110 --> 01:05:44,420
[Wu Yeol can't say anything]

1152
01:05:45,460 --> 01:05:49,710
There's a movie I've wanted to watch.

1153
01:05:49,710 --> 01:05:52,080
Do you watch movies?

1154
01:05:52,080 --> 01:05:53,350
Of course.

1155
01:05:53,400 --> 01:05:55,600
- What was that one called?
- "Once We Were Us"?

1156
01:05:55,600 --> 01:05:59,030
- I want to watch it.
- Yes, I want to, too.

1157
01:05:59,030 --> 01:06:03,830
[The same movie he promised
to watch with Yu Gyeong]

1158
01:06:05,000 --> 01:06:08,760
Is it still playing in theaters?

1159
01:06:16,040 --> 01:06:17,700
[The same movie...]

1160
01:06:17,700 --> 01:06:19,640
- The same movie. What do you do?
- I know.

1161
01:06:19,640 --> 01:06:22,520
It's big trouble.
The three should go together.

1162
01:06:22,520 --> 01:06:23,880
Oh, no.

1163
01:06:24,880 --> 01:06:30,000
To be honest, I don't want to do
anything with everyone there.

1164
01:06:32,130 --> 01:06:35,360
I want to pick a separate time...

1165
01:06:35,360 --> 01:06:38,380
Either watch separately...

1166
01:06:39,800 --> 01:06:43,440
[Earlier]
Was it this way?

1167
01:06:43,440 --> 01:06:46,950
It closes at 7 p.m. Is that okay?

1168
01:06:49,270 --> 01:06:51,600
Want to run?

1169
01:06:51,600 --> 01:06:54,360
We should run and look around.

1170
01:06:54,360 --> 01:06:56,370
[The two stopped by a store]

1171
01:06:56,370 --> 01:06:58,140
Cute socks.

1172
01:06:58,140 --> 01:07:00,420
There are so many different kinds.

1173
01:07:01,610 --> 01:07:03,770
Should we buy a pair?

1174
01:07:05,000 --> 01:07:07,490
Should we pick one for each other?

1175
01:07:07,490 --> 01:07:09,760
I usually wear black socks.

1176
01:07:09,760 --> 01:07:12,600
- Then...
- I'll go for a change.

1177
01:07:12,600 --> 01:07:16,020
But you must wear them one day.

1178
01:07:16,020 --> 01:07:18,370
- All right.
- You have to wear them, okay?

1179
01:07:18,370 --> 01:07:20,000
Then...

1180
01:07:20,960 --> 01:07:24,020
Green? Green...

1181
01:07:24,890 --> 01:07:28,140
I'll let you choose.

1182
01:07:29,480 --> 01:07:32,310
You wore yellow before. How about yellow?

1183
01:07:32,310 --> 01:07:34,680
I wanted to wear these.

1184
01:07:34,680 --> 01:07:36,510
Really? Then, I'll take these.

1185
01:07:36,510 --> 01:07:41,060
I gave them a pair he may not wear.

1186
01:07:41,060 --> 01:07:44,290
If he wears them,
that means he's willing, right?

1187
01:07:44,290 --> 01:07:46,260
She wanted to confirm that.

1188
01:07:46,260 --> 01:07:50,000
You said you went to
an izakaya last night, right?

1189
01:07:50,000 --> 01:07:54,210
You said you have a favorite spot.

1190
01:07:54,210 --> 01:07:56,080
Did you go there?

1191
01:07:57,140 --> 01:07:58,990
- No.
- Why not?

1192
01:07:58,990 --> 01:08:01,540
We went to a new spot
that I've never been to.

1193
01:08:02,450 --> 01:08:04,290
Didn't you choose?

1194
01:08:04,290 --> 01:08:05,800
I did.

1195
01:08:06,550 --> 01:08:09,330
But well...

1196
01:08:09,330 --> 01:08:13,120
I went to a new spot.
Somewhere I've never been to.

1197
01:08:15,640 --> 01:08:17,800
You didn't know who'd show up, right?

1198
01:08:17,800 --> 01:08:20,110
- You didn't know, right?
- Not at all.

1199
01:08:20,110 --> 01:08:22,830
I didn't know until I saw her.

1200
01:08:26,590 --> 01:08:29,380
She keeps wanting to check.

1201
01:08:31,010 --> 01:08:36,000
You know the movie with that
actor, Koo Kyo Hwan?

1202
01:08:36,000 --> 01:08:37,800
I want to see that.

1203
01:08:37,800 --> 01:08:42,010
But I'm afraid
it will leave the theaters soon.

1204
01:08:44,220 --> 01:08:45,840
[Glancing]

1205
01:08:46,690 --> 01:08:49,690
I think I should stop talking.

1206
01:08:49,690 --> 01:08:54,550
I feel like I'm giving you
too much information.

1207
01:08:55,400 --> 01:08:58,080
She's not suggesting
seeing the movie together.

1208
01:08:58,080 --> 01:09:01,530
[The talk of the movie fizzles out]

1209
01:09:01,530 --> 01:09:06,330
If someone you're not interested in at all

1210
01:09:06,330 --> 01:09:10,490
asks you out, do you go out with her?

1211
01:09:13,380 --> 01:09:16,700
When? About three to four weeks into it?

1212
01:09:16,700 --> 01:09:20,080
Of course, you wouldn't then.

1213
01:09:20,080 --> 01:09:22,470
- Right now?
- That'd be too easy.

1214
01:09:22,470 --> 01:09:24,480
Right now...

1215
01:09:26,210 --> 01:09:28,150
You'd get to know her?

1216
01:09:28,150 --> 01:09:30,180
For now.

1217
01:09:30,180 --> 01:09:32,050
I'm still...

1218
01:09:33,190 --> 01:09:40,030
wondering if I'm narrowing
my options too hastily.

1219
01:09:40,030 --> 01:09:42,880
I think I'd still talk to her.

1220
01:09:45,830 --> 01:09:47,600
Would you get out of it?

1221
01:09:47,600 --> 01:09:50,690
- Yeah.
- She says she'd get out of it.

1222
01:09:52,190 --> 01:09:55,860
Then, if I asked you out and
you gave me an excuse,

1223
01:09:55,860 --> 01:09:58,550
I should just catch on, huh?

1224
01:09:58,550 --> 01:10:01,310
[Cracking up]

1225
01:10:01,310 --> 01:10:03,820
Oh, got it.

1226
01:10:03,820 --> 01:10:06,390
"My office is moving..."

1227
01:10:15,380 --> 01:10:17,340
I'll remember that.

1228
01:10:18,180 --> 01:10:20,480
I have a good memory.

1229
01:10:22,150 --> 01:10:23,900
Oh, yeah?

1230
01:10:27,250 --> 01:10:29,060
[Ha...]

1231
01:10:29,060 --> 01:10:33,840
You keep me on my toes.

1232
01:10:33,840 --> 01:10:36,760
["You keep me on my toes"]

1233
01:10:36,760 --> 01:10:39,370
[Looking]

1234
01:10:39,370 --> 01:10:41,710
That's bad.

1235
01:10:41,710 --> 01:10:45,070
- I like it, though.
- I like talking.

1236
01:10:45,070 --> 01:10:47,420
But I remember everything.

1237
01:10:52,200 --> 01:10:54,480
I'll keep an eye on you.

1238
01:10:55,450 --> 01:10:58,030
I'll keep an eye on you.

1239
01:10:58,030 --> 01:11:01,810
Gyu Ri opened up a lot about her feelings.

1240
01:11:03,060 --> 01:11:06,520
[Before they knew it, time had passed]

1241
01:11:06,520 --> 01:11:10,490
You tend to wear mostly black.

1242
01:11:10,490 --> 01:11:13,340
I only wear achromatic colors.

1243
01:11:15,380 --> 01:11:17,790
You wore a brown sweater before.

1244
01:11:17,790 --> 01:11:18,800
[Grin]

1245
01:11:20,190 --> 01:11:21,660
[Grin]

1246
01:11:24,060 --> 01:11:25,610
[Phew...]

1247
01:11:25,610 --> 01:11:27,220
So detailed.

1248
01:11:27,220 --> 01:11:32,090
All the information that they've
gathered about each other

1249
01:11:32,090 --> 01:11:34,420
- all poured out tonight.
- Totally.

1250
01:11:34,420 --> 01:11:38,080
And even then, they left a little distance.

1251
01:11:38,080 --> 01:11:41,190
I feel like I saw another side of Wu Yeol.

1252
01:11:41,190 --> 01:11:44,700
I can see how detailed he is.

1253
01:11:44,700 --> 01:11:46,410
I saw how cautious he was.

1254
01:11:46,410 --> 01:11:49,540
I'm giving Wu Yeol more props today.

1255
01:11:49,540 --> 01:11:51,980
When they're together one-on-one,

1256
01:11:51,980 --> 01:11:56,880
I thought he'd say only what
Gyu Ri would want to hear.

1257
01:11:56,880 --> 01:11:59,070
Gyu Ri kept trying
to get confirmation from him.

1258
01:11:59,070 --> 01:12:01,620
She kept asking him,
"Do you like me? Is it her or me?"

1259
01:12:01,620 --> 01:12:04,000
She kept asking in circles.

1260
01:12:04,000 --> 01:12:07,900
When I saw that he couldn't
give her a firm answer,

1261
01:12:07,900 --> 01:12:13,290
I felt like he was still being honest.

1262
01:12:13,290 --> 01:12:15,100
Still keeping an appropriate distance?

1263
01:12:15,100 --> 01:12:18,230
He could confuse her,
but he won't lie to her.

1264
01:12:18,230 --> 01:12:20,860
I liked that honesty about him.

1265
01:12:20,900 --> 01:12:24,700
For me, I'm so confused.

1266
01:12:24,730 --> 01:12:26,500
When he was out with So Yun,

1267
01:12:26,500 --> 01:12:30,230
he had a good tiki-taka with her
and went along.

1268
01:12:30,230 --> 01:12:34,300
And with Gyu Ri, he'd adjust to her energy.

1269
01:12:34,300 --> 01:12:37,620
But with Yu Gyeong, he doesn't have that.

1270
01:12:37,620 --> 01:12:41,120
What would she want to see in him?

1271
01:12:41,120 --> 01:12:43,770
Yu Gyeong doesn't seem to care about that.

1272
01:12:43,770 --> 01:12:47,440
I feel like if she really did
keep him on his toes,

1273
01:12:47,440 --> 01:12:49,570
I don't think he would've said that.

1274
01:12:49,570 --> 01:12:51,560
I guess that could be.

1275
01:12:51,560 --> 01:12:54,000
But you must wear them one day.

1276
01:12:54,000 --> 01:12:56,330
- All right.
- You have to wear them, okay?

1277
01:12:56,330 --> 01:12:57,750
Then...

1278
01:12:57,750 --> 01:13:00,350
[Gyu Ri buys him green socks that pop]

1279
01:13:00,350 --> 01:13:02,860
Green?

1280
01:13:02,860 --> 01:13:05,870
But so what if he wears them?
Is that a big deal?

1281
01:13:05,870 --> 01:13:08,000
She's looking at small things.

1282
01:13:08,000 --> 01:13:11,100
- That movie is the issue.
- That movie sure is the issue.

1283
01:13:11,160 --> 01:13:13,510
The fact that Gyu Ri is so delicate...

1284
01:13:13,510 --> 01:13:15,510
I am a little worried about that.

1285
01:13:15,510 --> 01:13:18,020
What do we do about the movie?

1286
01:13:19,710 --> 01:13:22,720
[Late evening in Tokushima]

1287
01:13:23,930 --> 01:13:26,310
[Seo Won and Min Ju are on a date]

1288
01:13:26,310 --> 01:13:29,180
Hello.

1289
01:13:30,140 --> 01:13:32,300
- Should we sit here?
- It's so nice.

1290
01:13:32,300 --> 01:13:35,800
- It's so cute here.
- I know.

1291
01:13:35,800 --> 01:13:37,980
It's a pancake cafe.

1292
01:13:37,980 --> 01:13:40,950
We ate dinner, so we can skip the pancakes.

1293
01:13:40,950 --> 01:13:42,180
Sounds good.

1294
01:13:42,180 --> 01:13:43,790
Excuse me.

1295
01:13:43,790 --> 01:13:48,070
Iced coffee and...

1296
01:13:48,070 --> 01:13:51,830
an iced cafe latte, please.

1297
01:13:53,380 --> 01:13:55,970
Thank you.

1298
01:13:55,970 --> 01:13:58,160
[Ordered properly]

1299
01:13:58,160 --> 01:14:02,260
The vibe here is...

1300
01:14:03,770 --> 01:14:05,370
cute.

1301
01:14:08,470 --> 01:14:11,580
- Why are you so nervous?
- What are you saying?

1302
01:14:13,600 --> 01:14:15,680
[Earlier in the restaurant]

1303
01:14:16,470 --> 01:14:19,650
[Seong Min asked Yu Gyeong out
in front of Min Ju]

1304
01:14:19,650 --> 01:14:22,350
It keeps coming out.
That scene was so shocking.

1305
01:14:22,350 --> 01:14:23,700
[Upset]

1306
01:14:23,700 --> 01:14:27,710
It's worse since they had talked.
If they didn't talk at all...

1307
01:14:27,710 --> 01:14:29,770
That's all she can think about.

1308
01:14:30,770 --> 01:14:34,620
[Min Ju is feeling uneasy]

1309
01:14:34,620 --> 01:14:37,630
- Why can't you talk?
- What do you mean?

1310
01:14:37,630 --> 01:14:41,430
I'm just waiting in silence.

1311
01:14:42,340 --> 01:14:45,790
You should learn to enjoy silence.

1312
01:14:47,990 --> 01:14:53,510
[She's different than usual]

1313
01:14:54,510 --> 01:14:57,230
Thank you.

1314
01:14:57,230 --> 01:15:01,600
It's true. We've never hung out
together. Not at all.

1315
01:15:01,600 --> 01:15:05,060
I just remember going grocery shopping

1316
01:15:05,060 --> 01:15:07,770
and cooking with you on Day 2.

1317
01:15:07,770 --> 01:15:10,240
- We've never talked since.
- Right.

1318
01:15:10,240 --> 01:15:13,380
- We never had a chance to.
- I know.

1319
01:15:13,380 --> 01:15:16,530
There was no set rule. So, I just said it.

1320
01:15:16,530 --> 01:15:21,740
Yeah, I liked that. But I guess
I thought of this as an MT.

1321
01:15:21,740 --> 01:15:25,060
- It felt like MT...
- You were relaxed.

1322
01:15:25,060 --> 01:15:29,610
I was relaxed, but when that
topic was brought up...

1323
01:15:29,610 --> 01:15:32,020
I think I struggled.

1324
01:15:32,020 --> 01:15:34,230
- Were you taken aback?
- Yes, I was.

1325
01:15:34,230 --> 01:15:38,560
I thought, "Would I be okay
if this keeps happening?"

1326
01:15:38,560 --> 01:15:40,600
So, my thoughts were jumbled.

1327
01:15:40,600 --> 01:15:43,490
Would you be okay? In what way?

1328
01:15:43,490 --> 01:15:47,240
I'd have to face some things
that I don't want to.

1329
01:15:47,240 --> 01:15:50,890
- We always have to make a choice.
- Right.

1330
01:15:50,890 --> 01:15:53,590
Who did you go on dates with?

1331
01:15:53,590 --> 01:15:56,710
You had dinner with Jun Hyeon, right?

1332
01:15:57,710 --> 01:15:58,990
I think you two are so different.

1333
01:15:59,000 --> 01:16:01,220
I wouldn't know
since I don't go out with guys.

1334
01:16:01,220 --> 01:16:02,300
Jun Hyeon?

1335
01:16:02,310 --> 01:16:05,220
[On the plane to Japan]

1336
01:16:05,220 --> 01:16:08,610
[Jun Hyeon sat next to Min Ju]

1337
01:16:09,810 --> 01:16:12,630
Did you get used to the environment?
How are you?

1338
01:16:12,630 --> 01:16:14,800
Me? I'm always adjusting.

1339
01:16:14,800 --> 01:16:16,500
Min Ju is reaching out first.

1340
01:16:16,500 --> 01:16:17,880
[Min Ju broke the silence first]

1341
01:16:19,100 --> 01:16:22,190
Talk to me if you're struggling.
I'll listen to you.

1342
01:16:22,190 --> 01:16:24,110
- Really?
- Yes.

1343
01:16:25,130 --> 01:16:29,190
Then, who do you talk to?

1344
01:16:30,600 --> 01:16:32,180
[Shaking her head]

1345
01:16:34,330 --> 01:16:37,800
Do you have concerns now? Do you worry a lot?

1346
01:16:38,930 --> 01:16:40,300
Would you hear me out?

1347
01:16:40,300 --> 01:16:43,730
Yeah, I'll hear you out. I want to know.

1348
01:16:46,400 --> 01:16:49,070
You remember our first date?

1349
01:16:49,070 --> 01:16:50,560
- Our date?
- She's hashing it out.

1350
01:16:50,560 --> 01:16:52,860
You said you can't talk to me.

1351
01:16:52,900 --> 01:16:56,170
- What are you saying?
- See? He doesn't know.

1352
01:16:56,170 --> 01:16:59,970
I said that's what I had thought.
I didn't say we can't talk.

1353
01:17:01,760 --> 01:17:05,580
You really... You got it all wrong.
You totally misunderstood me.

1354
01:17:05,580 --> 01:17:06,970
I'm so glad.

1355
01:17:06,970 --> 01:17:10,450
Why would I say that to you
even if it were the case?

1356
01:17:10,450 --> 01:17:12,640
I mean, are you dumb or something?

1357
01:17:12,640 --> 01:17:15,300
- What's wrong with you?
- He's not like that.

1358
01:17:15,300 --> 01:17:18,450
What a relief. I'm so glad.

1359
01:17:19,330 --> 01:17:22,090
Give me a minute.

1360
01:17:23,180 --> 01:17:27,470
- It's so...
- She felt bad about being upset.

1361
01:17:27,470 --> 01:17:29,540
Were you stressed out?

1362
01:17:29,540 --> 01:17:31,510
- Yeah.
- Really?

1363
01:17:31,510 --> 01:17:33,300
This is how they hash it out.

1364
01:17:33,300 --> 01:17:35,950
Did Min Ju have trouble sleeping, too?

1365
01:17:35,950 --> 01:17:37,800
[Worried, not knowing what really happened]

1366
01:17:37,800 --> 01:17:41,030
When we went out, you wanted
to open the car door.

1367
01:17:41,030 --> 01:17:42,930
And that scared me.

1368
01:17:42,930 --> 01:17:45,860
I thought I was going out with a psychopath.

1369
01:17:45,860 --> 01:17:47,210
They're good together.

1370
01:17:47,210 --> 01:17:49,810
I'm so happy to be on this trip to Japan.

1371
01:17:49,810 --> 01:17:51,920
Because we straightened it out.

1372
01:17:51,920 --> 01:17:53,770
That's good.

1373
01:17:53,770 --> 01:17:56,620
That's why I felt sick to my stomach and all.

1374
01:17:56,620 --> 01:17:58,550
And all that went away.

1375
01:17:58,550 --> 01:18:00,420
I feel so good right now.

1376
01:18:00,420 --> 01:18:03,650
I want to go running with you.
I want to go out right now.

1377
01:18:03,650 --> 01:18:06,900
Jun Hyeon is so cute.

1378
01:18:06,900 --> 01:18:10,380
- He's got a charm unlike how he looks.
- She said he's cute.

1379
01:18:10,380 --> 01:18:14,420
Yeah, I want to take care of him
and keep thinking about him.

1380
01:18:14,420 --> 01:18:16,370
He's got some lovely qualities.

1381
01:18:16,370 --> 01:18:19,840
He looks like a little baby chick.

1382
01:18:19,840 --> 01:18:21,020
You know?

1383
01:18:21,020 --> 01:18:23,350
His lips look like this.

1384
01:18:23,350 --> 01:18:24,970
He looks like a baby chick.

1385
01:18:24,970 --> 01:18:27,670
And he's older.

1386
01:18:27,670 --> 01:18:29,720
A slight twist.

1387
01:18:32,180 --> 01:18:34,690
- Can I ask you a question?
- Huh?

1388
01:18:34,690 --> 01:18:38,330
- Can I ask you some questions I have?
- Yeah, sure, sure.

1389
01:18:38,330 --> 01:18:41,770
What kind of person did you want
to meet when you came here?

1390
01:18:41,800 --> 01:18:45,800
As in your ideal type. What you seek.

1391
01:18:53,480 --> 01:18:55,370
Someone I can talk to.

1392
01:18:55,370 --> 01:18:57,820
- Someone to talk to?
- It's so crucial.

1393
01:18:57,820 --> 01:19:01,660
For the first time, I realized
conversations over appearance here.

1394
01:19:01,660 --> 01:19:02,690
- Here?
- Yes.

1395
01:19:02,690 --> 01:19:05,380
When you talked to someone
based on first impressions.

1396
01:19:05,400 --> 01:19:07,800
- It was so different.
- That's true.

1397
01:19:07,800 --> 01:19:13,220
I didn't want to fall in love at first sight

1398
01:19:13,220 --> 01:19:16,860
like I used to in the past.

1399
01:19:16,860 --> 01:19:21,830
And you know, it felt like I was off
to a good start when I arrived.

1400
01:19:21,830 --> 01:19:27,190
I didn't fall for someone
I went "Oh!" at first sight.

1401
01:19:27,190 --> 01:19:30,020
I was drawn to someone
I could easily talk to.

1402
01:19:30,020 --> 01:19:33,680
I realized that I was growing as a person.

1403
01:19:33,680 --> 01:19:35,800
- That's a great sign.
- I know.

1404
01:19:35,800 --> 01:19:37,720
- You must've been so proud.
- I am.

1405
01:19:37,720 --> 01:19:39,760
I'm so proud of myself.

1406
01:19:40,700 --> 01:19:43,910
Are you worried about anything specific?

1407
01:19:43,910 --> 01:19:49,400
Where someone I like is interested
in someone else.

1408
01:19:49,400 --> 01:19:51,750
Of course, I've already imagined that.

1409
01:19:51,750 --> 01:19:53,940
And there are texts.

1410
01:19:53,940 --> 01:19:57,230
But just because they don't show
interest in me with those texts,

1411
01:19:57,230 --> 01:20:01,020
I don't think "I should stop
liking that person now."

1412
01:20:01,020 --> 01:20:04,280
I learned that for sure in the past few days.

1413
01:20:05,580 --> 01:20:09,590
If I like that person,
even if she doesn't like me back,

1414
01:20:09,590 --> 01:20:11,620
I think I'll still like her.

1415
01:20:14,000 --> 01:20:17,070
And if things don't work out,
I can't help that.

1416
01:20:17,070 --> 01:20:19,100
But I'll try my best until the end.

1417
01:20:19,100 --> 01:20:22,700
If I'm sure about the person. That's all.

1418
01:20:23,710 --> 01:20:27,190
I feel like they're consoling each other.

1419
01:20:27,190 --> 01:20:33,380
[Having a deep conversation
for the first time]

1420
01:20:34,300 --> 01:20:38,000
It's already been a week.

1421
01:20:38,000 --> 01:20:41,060
And I feel a little jealous.

1422
01:20:41,060 --> 01:20:44,180
- Really?
- Jealousy?

1423
01:20:44,180 --> 01:20:48,020
I want to express that I'm jealous.
But I'm holding back.

1424
01:20:48,020 --> 01:20:51,090
But I felt that. I had no idea I would.

1425
01:20:51,090 --> 01:20:54,890
- I didn't know I'd be like this.
- Yeah, but...

1426
01:20:54,890 --> 01:20:57,760
It's complex. That's why everyone struggles.

1427
01:20:57,760 --> 01:21:00,810
[Identifying with him]

1428
01:21:01,310 --> 01:21:03,810
I'm awe-inspired.

1429
01:21:03,810 --> 01:21:07,540
I just thought you were always cheerful

1430
01:21:07,540 --> 01:21:09,910
and expressed yourself directly.

1431
01:21:09,910 --> 01:21:13,120
Even your laughs are earnest.

1432
01:21:13,120 --> 01:21:16,960
- I hear that I'm very transparent.
- You are.

1433
01:21:16,960 --> 01:21:24,830
I felt like we had a middle
schooler in the midst of us.

1434
01:21:27,400 --> 01:21:29,640
Right. That's true. He's pure and...

1435
01:21:29,640 --> 01:21:32,190
[Very pure and transparent]

1436
01:21:32,190 --> 01:21:35,260
I didn't think you had depth.

1437
01:21:35,260 --> 01:21:37,090
So, I'm so surprised.

1438
01:21:37,090 --> 01:21:38,950
Really?

1439
01:21:38,950 --> 01:21:41,800
And you're always listening to music
and writing.

1440
01:21:41,800 --> 01:21:44,670
I just thought you were in your world.

1441
01:21:45,650 --> 01:21:48,970
That I'm into myself alone, huh?

1442
01:21:48,970 --> 01:21:55,050
Yeah, so I wondered if I could
share such a world with you.

1443
01:21:56,250 --> 01:21:58,220
You don't know people
unless you talk to them.

1444
01:21:58,220 --> 01:22:01,030
- Really.
- That's why we should converse.

1445
01:22:03,360 --> 01:22:04,480
It was a healing time.

1446
01:22:04,480 --> 01:22:05,610
[Totally healing]

1447
01:22:05,610 --> 01:22:07,650
Min Ju must be hurting the most.

1448
01:22:07,650 --> 01:22:10,130
She had a connection with Yu Gyeong.

1449
01:22:10,130 --> 01:22:16,870
But both Jun Hyeon and
Seong Min are into Yu Gyeong.

1450
01:22:16,870 --> 01:22:18,740
She didn't even have anyone to talk to.

1451
01:22:18,740 --> 01:22:21,870
And Seo Won became someone she could talk to.

1452
01:22:21,870 --> 01:22:25,400
She can't even talk to Yu Gyeong
about this stuff.

1453
01:22:25,400 --> 01:22:27,950
Seo Won seems to give off positive energy.

1454
01:22:27,950 --> 01:22:29,710
But it has to turn into a romance.

1455
01:22:29,710 --> 01:22:32,820
But while you're consoling each other

1456
01:22:32,820 --> 01:22:35,450
or hearing their dating issues,

1457
01:22:35,450 --> 01:22:37,690
I can't imagine falling for the person...

1458
01:22:37,690 --> 01:22:39,100
But that happens a lot.

1459
01:22:39,100 --> 01:22:42,600
- Even in dramas or movies.
- In reality, too.

1460
01:22:42,600 --> 01:22:45,680
There are instances
where two fall for each other

1461
01:22:45,680 --> 01:22:47,900
while consoling a breakup.

1462
01:22:47,900 --> 01:22:50,080
It happens a lot in life.

1463
01:22:50,080 --> 01:22:52,380
[How will it turn out?]

1464
01:22:52,380 --> 01:22:55,140
- Is it there?
- That's it. I found this place.

1465
01:22:55,140 --> 01:22:56,700
Really?

1466
01:22:56,700 --> 01:23:01,400
- It's a chicken specialty place.
- Really? Looks good.

1467
01:23:02,650 --> 01:23:03,930
Thank you.

1468
01:23:03,930 --> 01:23:05,860
The chicken is the main dish.

1469
01:23:05,860 --> 01:23:07,600
[Bow]

1470
01:23:07,600 --> 01:23:10,960
Oh-ho. It's pretty spacious.

1471
01:23:10,960 --> 01:23:13,200
It's so warm here.

1472
01:23:14,180 --> 01:23:17,060
[What is going to happen here?]

1473
01:23:17,060 --> 01:23:19,210
Thank you.

1474
01:23:19,210 --> 01:23:21,120
Cheers.

1475
01:23:21,120 --> 01:23:23,870
How much did you say you drink?

1476
01:23:23,870 --> 01:23:25,730
I won't get drunk.

1477
01:23:26,540 --> 01:23:28,240
[Laugh]

1478
01:23:28,240 --> 01:23:30,560
Take your time at your own pace.

1479
01:23:32,230 --> 01:23:33,740
[Gulp]

1480
01:23:37,080 --> 01:23:39,130
- Daebak
- That was quite a sip.

1481
01:23:39,130 --> 01:23:41,230
But wait...

1482
01:23:41,230 --> 01:23:42,440
That was quite a sip.

1483
01:23:42,440 --> 01:23:44,860
Did they put whipped cream on top here?

1484
01:23:44,860 --> 01:23:47,090
- I asked for whipped cream on top.
- Right?

1485
01:23:47,090 --> 01:23:48,410
[Love it]

1486
01:23:48,410 --> 01:23:53,550
Of course.
This is on a different level, right?

1487
01:23:53,550 --> 01:23:57,920
I get it.
It's on a completely different level.

1488
01:23:57,920 --> 01:24:01,360
- Is it amazing?
- It's amazing. Daebak.

1489
01:24:01,360 --> 01:24:02,710
Nice choice.

1490
01:24:02,710 --> 01:24:04,150
[Got Yu Gyeong's approval]

1491
01:24:04,150 --> 01:24:06,740
So, can we speak casually after a drink?

1492
01:24:06,740 --> 01:24:08,210
It's about time.

1493
01:24:08,210 --> 01:24:09,730
Of course.

1494
01:24:09,730 --> 01:24:12,180
Because you didn't give me a chance.

1495
01:24:12,180 --> 01:24:15,360
I found a crack. A chance to speak casually.

1496
01:24:15,360 --> 01:24:18,140
I'd love that.

1497
01:24:19,820 --> 01:24:21,200
[Guzzle]

1498
01:24:21,200 --> 01:24:23,340
Seong Min wants to get drunk.

1499
01:24:23,340 --> 01:24:24,630
[Ta-da]

1500
01:24:24,630 --> 01:24:25,300
[In shock]

1501
01:24:25,300 --> 01:24:28,130
What? Three sips?

1502
01:24:28,130 --> 01:24:30,380
Let's say two and a half.

1503
01:24:30,380 --> 01:24:31,950
It's a good draft beer.

1504
01:24:31,950 --> 01:24:33,670
- Speak casually.
- Okay.

1505
01:24:33,670 --> 01:24:36,280
And for me...

1506
01:24:36,280 --> 01:24:37,880
- You won't speak casually?
- I prefer honorifics.

1507
01:24:37,880 --> 01:24:42,440
- That's right.
- I don't like how too comfortable

1508
01:24:42,440 --> 01:24:44,910
I become if I speak casually.

1509
01:24:45,800 --> 01:24:49,530
Can't you make me feel comfortable, though?

1510
01:24:49,530 --> 01:24:52,250
Really? You like that better?

1511
01:24:52,250 --> 01:24:55,440
- I feel so distant.
- Really?

1512
01:24:55,440 --> 01:24:57,840
- A little later.
- A little later?

1513
01:24:59,340 --> 01:25:00,990
Then...

1514
01:25:01,750 --> 01:25:03,180
[Laugh]

1515
01:25:03,910 --> 01:25:06,230
This is crazy.

1516
01:25:06,230 --> 01:25:08,140
My heart hurts.

1517
01:25:08,140 --> 01:25:10,150
Your heart dropped?

1518
01:25:11,110 --> 01:25:12,420
My top secret notebook.

1519
01:25:12,420 --> 01:25:14,730
- I'm so curious.
- Let's see.

1520
01:25:14,730 --> 01:25:15,960
[Excited]

1521
01:25:16,560 --> 01:25:19,400
Kang Yu Gyeong, college student.

1522
01:25:19,400 --> 01:25:22,070
- Studying modern dance. Born in 2004.
- Wait.

1523
01:25:22,100 --> 01:25:24,900
- What?
- Modern dance?

1524
01:25:29,570 --> 01:25:32,300
Wait, wait. Sorry, sorry.

1525
01:25:32,300 --> 01:25:33,470
[No idea]

1526
01:25:33,470 --> 01:25:35,430
Modern... what should I say?

1527
01:25:35,430 --> 01:25:37,200
- Korean dance.
- Sorry, sorry.

1528
01:25:37,200 --> 01:25:39,400
- It's totally different.
- Sorry. I didn't know. Really.

1529
01:25:39,430 --> 01:25:42,000
- Sir.
- So different.

1530
01:25:42,000 --> 01:25:43,800
Difference between jazz
and Korean traditional music.

1531
01:25:43,800 --> 01:25:45,600
That's right.

1532
01:25:45,650 --> 01:25:49,340
Did you hear wrong? Did you not
know it was a Korean dance?

1533
01:25:49,340 --> 01:25:50,980
- Yes.
- Really?

1534
01:25:50,980 --> 01:25:53,220
Please correct it.

1535
01:25:53,220 --> 01:25:54,160
[Pursing lips]

1536
01:25:54,160 --> 01:25:55,840
Korean dance.

1537
01:25:55,840 --> 01:25:57,710
Traditional dance.

1538
01:25:57,710 --> 01:25:58,810
Traditional dance...

1539
01:25:58,810 --> 01:26:00,800
["Korean Dance," writing down with emphasis]

1540
01:26:01,180 --> 01:26:02,630
[Laugh]

1541
01:26:02,630 --> 01:26:05,720
I heard it and tried to remember.

1542
01:26:05,720 --> 01:26:07,760
And since we didn't know...

1543
01:26:07,760 --> 01:26:08,840
- He's flustered.
- It could happen.

1544
01:26:08,840 --> 01:26:10,130
I'm sorry.

1545
01:26:10,130 --> 01:26:13,360
If it were in my field, it would
be like saying I'm a dentist.

1546
01:26:13,360 --> 01:26:16,550
It's like calling me
an oriental medicine doctor.

1547
01:26:16,550 --> 01:26:18,880
Since you said you were a doctor.

1548
01:26:18,880 --> 01:26:21,030
Yes. I'm sorry. Traditional dance.

1549
01:26:21,030 --> 01:26:23,540
He feels awkward.

1550
01:26:23,540 --> 01:26:26,710
- This is so good.
- I think it's super hot.

1551
01:26:27,620 --> 01:26:29,200
W-W-Wait...

1552
01:26:29,200 --> 01:26:30,890
It didn't splash, right?

1553
01:26:30,890 --> 01:26:33,020
- It was so hot.
- Right.

1554
01:26:33,020 --> 01:26:36,620
Put one more and cool it down.

1555
01:26:36,620 --> 01:26:37,970
Okay.

1556
01:26:37,970 --> 01:26:41,440
This is fun. Are you enjoying life?

1557
01:26:41,440 --> 01:26:45,010
My life is nothing without studying.

1558
01:26:45,880 --> 01:26:49,120
I'm not being annoying,
but all I did was study.

1559
01:26:49,200 --> 01:26:52,200
"No fun person." Not "braised."

1560
01:26:52,200 --> 01:26:56,370
I'm "no fun person."

1561
01:26:56,370 --> 01:26:57,810
But you know...

1562
01:26:57,810 --> 01:27:02,960
for me, all I did was dance.

1563
01:27:03,920 --> 01:27:06,990
- That's all I had.
- She's speaking casually.

1564
01:27:07,940 --> 01:27:10,190
It was tough for you.

1565
01:27:10,190 --> 01:27:12,520
- What's going on?
- What?

1566
01:27:12,520 --> 01:27:14,610
What's going on?

1567
01:27:14,610 --> 01:27:16,770
- What's going on?
- Is someone here?

1568
01:27:16,770 --> 01:27:18,900
[Seo Won and Min Ju show up]

1569
01:27:18,900 --> 01:27:21,000
- What's going on?
- Are we sitting together?

1570
01:27:21,000 --> 01:27:23,230
I'm glad. They're both...

1571
01:27:23,230 --> 01:27:26,200
Wait, how about Min Ju? No, no.

1572
01:27:26,200 --> 01:27:29,000
No, that's not good. This is weird.

1573
01:27:29,000 --> 01:27:33,290
- This will get weird.
- Right. Seong Min makes it obvious.

1574
01:27:33,290 --> 01:27:34,510
[Stunned]

1575
01:27:34,510 --> 01:27:38,510
Didn't you know we were joining you?

1576
01:27:38,510 --> 01:27:40,910
What? Unbelievable.

1577
01:27:40,910 --> 01:27:42,850
We were having a good time.

1578
01:27:42,850 --> 01:27:44,850
I know. These people...

1579
01:27:44,850 --> 01:27:46,370
What's that?

1580
01:27:46,370 --> 01:27:48,480
- What did you guys do?
- So sudden.

1581
01:27:48,480 --> 01:27:51,260
We were at a cafe.

1582
01:27:51,260 --> 01:27:53,740
- We knew, though.
- We didn't know.

1583
01:27:53,740 --> 01:27:55,490
I didn't know with whom.

1584
01:27:55,490 --> 01:27:57,810
Their draft beer is awesome.

1585
01:27:57,810 --> 01:28:00,150
It's awesome here.

1586
01:28:00,150 --> 01:28:02,050
- It's so good to see you guys.
- Liar.

1587
01:28:02,050 --> 01:28:03,980
Good to see you. Really.

1588
01:28:03,980 --> 01:28:07,020
- Seong Min could feel uncomfortable.
- Hey.

1589
01:28:07,020 --> 01:28:10,720
What's with you? When did you spray it?

1590
01:28:10,720 --> 01:28:13,530
- What do you mean?
- What did you do?

1591
01:28:13,530 --> 01:28:15,740
- Is this pork?
- What did you do?

1592
01:28:15,740 --> 01:28:16,710
What did you talk about?

1593
01:28:16,710 --> 01:28:19,330
Chicken. Their chicken is really good.

1594
01:28:19,330 --> 01:28:21,650
Really? They look good.

1595
01:28:21,650 --> 01:28:23,920
Let's order some more.

1596
01:28:23,920 --> 01:28:27,610
- Water?
- Yeah, I'll get water.

1597
01:28:27,610 --> 01:28:30,810
[Seo Won orders a drink
for Min Ju, who can't drink]

1598
01:28:30,810 --> 01:28:32,820
- Mango?
- Yeah, Mango.

1599
01:28:33,960 --> 01:28:35,490
It was our first time talking.

1600
01:28:35,490 --> 01:28:38,060
- It was our first time talking, too.
- Really?

1601
01:28:38,060 --> 01:28:39,580
It's a gathering of new meetups.

1602
01:28:39,580 --> 01:28:43,230
- It feels different to meet like this, huh?
- It feels weird.

1603
01:28:45,000 --> 01:28:48,990
[Strange energy in the air]

1604
01:28:50,170 --> 01:28:53,270
[New drinks and beers are served]

1605
01:28:53,270 --> 01:28:57,470
- Isn't this the green tangerine?
- Isn't it lime?

1606
01:28:57,470 --> 01:29:00,200
Did they get it wrong? We asked for mango.

1607
01:29:00,200 --> 01:29:02,860
- Mango.
- It's not alcohol, right?

1608
01:29:02,860 --> 01:29:04,850
I'm going to the restroom.

1609
01:29:04,850 --> 01:29:07,230
[Reordering a Coke]

1610
01:29:08,490 --> 01:29:09,880
Did you have fun?

1611
01:29:09,880 --> 01:29:12,020
[Mumbling]

1612
01:29:12,020 --> 01:29:13,400
Were you at a cafe before this?

1613
01:29:13,400 --> 01:29:16,050
Yes, we came from a cafe.

1614
01:29:16,050 --> 01:29:18,680
Should we speak casually, too?

1615
01:29:18,680 --> 01:29:20,740
I'm really trying hard.

1616
01:29:20,740 --> 01:29:24,000
Really? You decided to open your heart now?

1617
01:29:24,000 --> 01:29:26,310
You seem so closed up.

1618
01:29:26,310 --> 01:29:28,730
No, I had my reasons. Right?

1619
01:29:28,730 --> 01:29:31,760
He didn't want to be influenced by age.
To get to know us slowly.

1620
01:29:31,760 --> 01:29:32,800
He's very serious.

1621
01:29:32,800 --> 01:29:35,190
Whether it's an older or a younger woman?

1622
01:29:35,190 --> 01:29:39,260
I promised him that
we'd speak casually in Japan.

1623
01:29:39,260 --> 01:29:41,280
So, are you guys speaking casually?

1624
01:29:41,280 --> 01:29:42,730
We are.

1625
01:29:43,620 --> 01:29:45,930
Then, speak comfortably.

1626
01:29:45,930 --> 01:29:48,870
O-Okay. Good to see you.

1627
01:29:50,260 --> 01:29:53,290
- You want some beer? Should I order?
- Sounds good.

1628
01:29:53,290 --> 01:29:55,790
Okay, Yu Gyeong.

1629
01:29:55,790 --> 01:29:57,290
Yeah.

1630
01:29:59,940 --> 01:30:02,830
I can call you "Oppa," right?

1631
01:30:02,830 --> 01:30:04,030
Seong Min...

1632
01:30:04,030 --> 01:30:07,530
You can just say "Hey." Really.
If you feel comfortable.

1633
01:30:07,530 --> 01:30:10,580
- I don't want to.
- I'm fine with that.

1634
01:30:10,580 --> 01:30:14,170
Out of the four ladies,

1635
01:30:14,170 --> 01:30:17,900
I think I spoke the least with Min Ju.

1636
01:30:17,900 --> 01:30:19,270
- Really?
- That's why...

1637
01:30:19,270 --> 01:30:22,370
I picked her out and spoke up today.

1638
01:30:22,370 --> 01:30:25,120
The day after we moved in...

1639
01:30:25,120 --> 01:30:26,610
[Vroom]

1640
01:30:26,610 --> 01:30:28,240
Did I go too fast?

1641
01:30:28,240 --> 01:30:29,920
- No, no.
- It was cool.

1642
01:30:29,920 --> 01:30:32,070
You stepped up, so I went for it, too.

1643
01:30:32,070 --> 01:30:33,340
- Good job.
- "Yu Gyeong for me."

1644
01:30:33,340 --> 01:30:35,520
Two people who went fast.

1645
01:30:37,260 --> 01:30:39,380
I wonder how we're going to decide tomorrow.

1646
01:30:39,380 --> 01:30:42,050
Do women get to choose tomorrow?

1647
01:30:42,050 --> 01:30:44,770
I'll do this. "You, come out."

1648
01:30:44,770 --> 01:30:48,700
Actually, we punched each other outside.

1649
01:30:48,700 --> 01:30:51,760
I won't go easy on you
just because you're older.

1650
01:30:51,760 --> 01:30:53,280
I beat him up and won.

1651
01:30:53,280 --> 01:30:54,920
[He beat up Jun Hyeon?]

1652
01:30:58,460 --> 01:30:59,860
Fair and square.

1653
01:30:59,860 --> 01:31:01,840
- What did you say?
- Fair and square.

1654
01:31:01,840 --> 01:31:03,790
Fair and square?

1655
01:31:03,790 --> 01:31:09,520
He keeps saying how fiercely
he fought for her in front of Min Ju.

1656
01:31:09,520 --> 01:31:12,420
So, tell me what you guys talked about.

1657
01:31:13,820 --> 01:31:16,080
To tell you everything...

1658
01:31:16,080 --> 01:31:18,360
Wait, let me get my journal.

1659
01:31:18,360 --> 01:31:20,240
He wrote it down while we were talking.

1660
01:31:20,240 --> 01:31:21,640
Really?

1661
01:31:22,500 --> 01:31:23,810
I jot it down on the bus.

1662
01:31:23,810 --> 01:31:25,190
You took notes while talking?

1663
01:31:25,190 --> 01:31:26,820
No. I'm kidding.

1664
01:31:26,820 --> 01:31:30,000
It's not that. It was like this.

1665
01:31:30,000 --> 01:31:31,950
There was an error.

1666
01:31:31,950 --> 01:31:34,130
They bring up what only the two
of them know about.

1667
01:31:34,130 --> 01:31:36,940
Korean traditional dance.

1668
01:31:36,940 --> 01:31:37,950
[Glum]

1669
01:31:37,950 --> 01:31:40,200
Do you know what type of dance I do?

1670
01:31:41,630 --> 01:31:42,680
Modern?

1671
01:31:42,680 --> 01:31:44,300
See? That's what I mean.

1672
01:31:44,300 --> 01:31:46,000
[Escaping]

1673
01:31:46,000 --> 01:31:48,810
- I'm sorry.
- Korean dance.

1674
01:31:48,810 --> 01:31:50,530
That's Korean dance.

1675
01:31:50,530 --> 01:31:52,160
That's it.

1676
01:31:52,160 --> 01:31:54,060
I knew it.

1677
01:31:54,060 --> 01:31:55,400
[Stare]

1678
01:31:56,030 --> 01:31:57,410
[Solemn]

1679
01:31:58,480 --> 01:32:01,310
What did you two talk about?

1680
01:32:01,310 --> 01:32:03,800
What? Why do you have your guard up?

1681
01:32:03,800 --> 01:32:05,780
I'm so curious.

1682
01:32:05,780 --> 01:32:09,560
You know, for us...

1683
01:32:09,560 --> 01:32:12,530
It was our first time, but we
had a constructive conversation.

1684
01:32:12,530 --> 01:32:14,570
Yeah, it was complete.

1685
01:32:14,570 --> 01:32:17,230
Complete?

1686
01:32:17,230 --> 01:32:18,780
Not yet for me.

1687
01:32:19,960 --> 01:32:22,310
I'm still working on it.

1688
01:32:22,310 --> 01:32:23,570
Still working on it?

1689
01:32:23,570 --> 01:32:27,350
- We had a very healthy conversation.
- Right. Really.

1690
01:32:27,350 --> 01:32:28,490
It left an impression.

1691
01:32:28,490 --> 01:32:33,390
[Drinking to everyone's completion]

1692
01:32:34,690 --> 01:32:36,330
What's this? I'm having fun.

1693
01:32:36,330 --> 01:32:37,420
[Smile]

1694
01:32:38,390 --> 01:32:41,260
This is a first for the four of us.

1695
01:32:41,260 --> 01:32:43,890
True. It feels new to meet as four.

1696
01:32:43,890 --> 01:32:45,790
Right.

1697
01:32:45,790 --> 01:32:48,390
It's so good to run into you here.

1698
01:32:48,390 --> 01:32:50,670
It's different than
eating as a group of eight.

1699
01:32:50,670 --> 01:32:54,250
[Settling into a drinking party]

1700
01:32:54,940 --> 01:32:58,270
- It's nice. I finally got rid of my bias.
- What bias?

1701
01:32:58,270 --> 01:33:01,260
About traveling?

1702
01:33:02,870 --> 01:33:04,750
It's so nice.

1703
01:33:04,750 --> 01:33:06,530
I won't be able to sleep tonight.

1704
01:33:06,530 --> 01:33:08,740
I won't sleep.

1705
01:33:08,740 --> 01:33:11,970
I can drink until I get plastered today.

1706
01:33:17,220 --> 01:33:20,710
So, you're slowing yourself down?

1707
01:33:20,710 --> 01:33:22,700
What about?

1708
01:33:22,700 --> 01:33:24,660
Slowing down your emotions?

1709
01:33:24,660 --> 01:33:26,000
[Shaking her head]

1710
01:33:26,000 --> 01:33:26,990
[Don't know]

1711
01:33:27,870 --> 01:33:30,080
[What did Min Ju's reaction mean?]

1712
01:33:30,080 --> 01:33:33,790
When we saw the whirlpool earlier...

1713
01:33:33,790 --> 01:33:37,490
I was thinking how glad I was to come here.

1714
01:33:37,490 --> 01:33:41,120
The time here felt so valuable.

1715
01:33:41,120 --> 01:33:46,000
The people I was with,
the scenery, and the situation.

1716
01:33:46,000 --> 01:33:48,610
It was so nice.

1717
01:33:48,610 --> 01:33:50,320
Let's take lots of pictures.

1718
01:33:50,320 --> 01:33:53,230
[Spending the time they want to hold onto]

1719
01:33:54,060 --> 01:33:56,490
- It was good, huh?
- It was good.

1720
01:33:56,490 --> 01:33:58,820
The draft beer was good, too.

1721
01:33:58,820 --> 01:34:03,320
It was good timing.
Yu Gyeong is interested in Wu Yeol.

1722
01:34:03,320 --> 01:34:06,910
But he won't give her confirmation.

1723
01:34:06,910 --> 01:34:10,790
But Seong Min doesn't confuse her,
and he approaches her honestly.

1724
01:34:10,790 --> 01:34:13,430
I think she could think
that was a cool quality.

1725
01:34:13,430 --> 01:34:16,390
- That's no use.
- Really?

1726
01:34:16,390 --> 01:34:18,260
[LOL]

1727
01:34:18,260 --> 01:34:20,520
I don't think he moved Yu Gyeong's heart.

1728
01:34:20,520 --> 01:34:23,210
It made her think of him even more.

1729
01:34:23,210 --> 01:34:26,290
If you've fallen as Yu Gyeong has,

1730
01:34:26,290 --> 01:34:28,800
- nothing matters.
- True.

1731
01:34:28,800 --> 01:34:31,510
Since they filmed in Japan,
I'll use this expression.

1732
01:34:31,510 --> 01:34:33,930
He has no yama.*
(Impact)

1733
01:34:33,930 --> 01:34:35,330
Seong Min has no yama.

1734
01:34:35,330 --> 01:34:39,400
There has to be one big charm.
But he's easy-going and nice.

1735
01:34:39,400 --> 01:34:40,460
[I think so]

1736
01:34:40,460 --> 01:34:44,100
But I think that's even better.

1737
01:34:44,100 --> 01:34:47,820
He's the type to stay with
someone and stay consistent.

1738
01:34:47,820 --> 01:34:51,250
When he tries to make an impact,
that'll be his downfall.

1739
01:34:51,250 --> 01:34:53,420
He's a good person.

1740
01:34:53,420 --> 01:34:55,910
He's like a brick house.

1741
01:34:55,910 --> 01:34:59,580
Very orderly and stable.

1742
01:34:59,580 --> 01:35:04,210
And Min Ju likes Seong Min
more than I thought.

1743
01:35:04,210 --> 01:35:05,770
Well, you know.

1744
01:35:05,770 --> 01:35:08,240
She could still smile around him,
but she couldn't.

1745
01:35:08,240 --> 01:35:12,120
How can you see someone
you like pursue your friend?

1746
01:35:12,120 --> 01:35:14,750
I'm starting to compare
Wu Yeol and Seong Min.

1747
01:35:14,750 --> 01:35:18,270
Wu Yeol doesn't stare into a person.

1748
01:35:18,270 --> 01:35:20,570
He looks at food and talks at the same time.

1749
01:35:20,570 --> 01:35:21,580
That's right.

1750
01:35:21,580 --> 01:35:23,600
He says something to hook you
into a conversation.

1751
01:35:23,600 --> 01:35:26,140
But Seong Min stares at her so much.

1752
01:35:26,140 --> 01:35:27,950
He was looking at her all the time.

1753
01:35:27,950 --> 01:35:30,960
He tends to look away when
his feelings are showing.

1754
01:35:30,960 --> 01:35:34,530
But Wu Yeol looks at you for about
three seconds at crucial moments.

1755
01:35:34,530 --> 01:35:38,420
[It's amazing]

1756
01:35:38,420 --> 01:35:40,370
[Jun Hyeon and So Yun's evening date]

1757
01:35:40,370 --> 01:35:42,350
Jun Hyeon and So Yun.

1758
01:35:44,020 --> 01:35:47,000
That looks like Namsan Tower.

1759
01:35:47,900 --> 01:35:50,640
- I hope it looks cool.
- I hope it's pretty there.

1760
01:35:50,640 --> 01:35:54,400
But for one thing, the stars are amazing.

1761
01:35:54,400 --> 01:35:56,510
- Orion.
- Amazing, huh?

1762
01:35:58,600 --> 01:36:02,040
[Once you climb up the stairs]

1763
01:36:02,810 --> 01:36:03,950
Is this it?

1764
01:36:03,950 --> 01:36:06,700
I see something.

1765
01:36:06,700 --> 01:36:13,100
[The night lights of Tokushima
are in front of them]

1766
01:36:13,140 --> 01:36:14,490
It's so pretty.

1767
01:36:14,490 --> 01:36:17,160
It feels different than Seoul's night view.

1768
01:36:17,160 --> 01:36:21,640
[Quiet and peaceful night in Tokushima]

1769
01:36:23,330 --> 01:36:25,350
This side looks prettier.

1770
01:36:26,340 --> 01:36:30,060
I didn't know, but it's a huge city.

1771
01:36:30,060 --> 01:36:31,530
So pretty.

1772
01:36:31,530 --> 01:36:34,000
It's similar to Namsan but different.

1773
01:36:34,000 --> 01:36:37,320
- It's nice.
- Right?

1774
01:36:37,320 --> 01:36:39,410
It's worth a visit.

1775
01:36:42,620 --> 01:36:44,690
That looks like the Han River.

1776
01:36:45,880 --> 01:36:48,070
How nice.

1777
01:36:48,070 --> 01:36:52,780
[Where you can see Tokushima at a glance]

1778
01:36:52,780 --> 01:36:55,570
[Gazing out into the imposing night view]

1779
01:36:56,180 --> 01:36:57,950
I choose Yu Gyeong, too.

1780
01:36:57,950 --> 01:37:01,370
That's right. She saw him pick someone else.

1781
01:37:02,560 --> 01:37:07,360
[Hesitant]

1782
01:37:08,220 --> 01:37:11,440
Do you like something familiar
or something new?

1783
01:37:12,570 --> 01:37:14,570
Familiar versus new?

1784
01:37:14,570 --> 01:37:16,060
That's a very important question.

1785
01:37:16,060 --> 01:37:18,140
She's asking him what she's contemplating.

1786
01:37:18,140 --> 01:37:20,900
If I had to choose, something familiar.

1787
01:37:20,900 --> 01:37:22,720
Something familiar.

1788
01:37:26,630 --> 01:37:29,810
[The day before]

1789
01:37:29,810 --> 01:37:34,250
[After his work in the morning,
Jun Hyeon is waiting for someone]

1790
01:37:35,200 --> 01:37:39,630
[He earned a date last night
due to his late start in the house]

1791
01:37:39,630 --> 01:37:43,620
[Who did Jun Hyeon choose?]

1792
01:37:45,720 --> 01:37:47,000
Hello.

1793
01:37:47,000 --> 01:37:49,690
[Jun Hyeon is on a date with So Yun]

1794
01:37:50,260 --> 01:37:51,380
[Generously]

1795
01:37:51,380 --> 01:37:53,980
Thank you.

1796
01:37:53,980 --> 01:37:56,480
You should have some meat, too.

1797
01:37:56,480 --> 01:37:58,300
Thank you.

1798
01:37:59,140 --> 01:38:02,250
What do you usually do?

1799
01:38:02,250 --> 01:38:06,080
During workdays, all I do is work and sleep.

1800
01:38:06,080 --> 01:38:08,310
Except for that, I don't do much.

1801
01:38:08,310 --> 01:38:10,210
I don't really have hobbies...

1802
01:38:11,210 --> 01:38:14,530
- Watching reels lying down?
- Watching reels lying down.

1803
01:38:14,530 --> 01:38:16,630
I do that during the day, too.

1804
01:38:16,630 --> 01:38:18,990
I know all the memes.

1805
01:38:20,710 --> 01:38:22,890
People are people.

1806
01:38:22,890 --> 01:38:26,780
But if you say that,
you sound like you don't work at all.

1807
01:38:26,780 --> 01:38:28,620
So, you just...

1808
01:38:28,620 --> 01:38:31,610
I like someone like that, too.

1809
01:38:31,610 --> 01:38:33,040
Someone easy-going like that?

1810
01:38:33,040 --> 01:38:36,950
I'm not really into go-getters.

1811
01:38:38,390 --> 01:38:40,700
I think she'd think I'm pathetic.

1812
01:38:43,060 --> 01:38:46,130
[Smile]

1813
01:38:51,000 --> 01:38:54,430
The more I got to know him,
the stranger he seemed.

1814
01:38:56,000 --> 01:39:00,710
He seemed a little familiar.

1815
01:39:00,710 --> 01:39:02,300
Yes.

1816
01:39:02,390 --> 01:39:05,610
[Thinking]

1817
01:39:10,410 --> 01:39:13,390
You seem very realistic.

1818
01:39:13,390 --> 01:39:15,360
- Me?
- Yes.

1819
01:39:15,360 --> 01:39:17,750
You seem pretty stern.

1820
01:39:17,750 --> 01:39:20,210
A lot of people think that.

1821
01:39:20,210 --> 01:39:22,660
So honestly, I was a little scared.

1822
